title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix shredded cheese, flour and butter.
Make a soft dough. Roll each olive in small ball of dough.
Place on cookie sheet or flat surface and freeze overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour soda and boiling water over dates and raisins.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, then egg.
Beat well; add flour and mix.
Pour in fruit mixture (including water) and pecans.
Mix.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook flour, sugar, eggs and reserved pineapple juice until thick.
Let mixture cool and fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and chill.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and raisins in a 1-quart casserole.
Beat together the milk, water and eggs.
Then add remaining ingredients until mixture is very smooth.
Pour over rice and raisin mixture. Place casserole in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until custard is firm and a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
When thick, add broth, cauliflower and onion.
Cook and stir until cauliflower and onion are tender.
Turn off heat.
Stir in half and half.
Serve.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain the beans, peas, pimento and corn.
Mix all ingredients except the last 4 and put in a glass dish.
In a saucepan, add the sugar, oil, vinegar and water.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes. Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Good if made several days ahead.

title: salt dough ornaments
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Gradually add water until mixture is a putty-like consistency.
Knead dough 5 minutes to thoroughly blend ingredients.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick on floured surface. Cut with cookie cutters, dipped in flour, if sticky.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini until tender.
Cut lengthwise; scoop out centers.
Chop centers; season with salt and pepper.
Add onion and bread crumbs; mix.
Add cheese and bread crumbs to make a sticky consistency.
Add butter when necessary.
Fill zucchini; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cut bacon into bite-size pieces after frying and draining on a paper towel.
Spread on bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs, cream and seasonings just enough to blend.
Stir in cheese; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes, or until pie shell is golden brown and filling is firm.
Serves 4 as an entree.

title: leg of lamb with spices
directions: Combine vinegar, oil and seasonings; pour over lamb.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours, turning often. Remove lamb, strain marinade and reserve.
Place potatoes, onions, chilies and garlic in a shallow roasting pan; pour 1/4 cup marinade over vegetables.
Place lamb on roasting rack over vegetables.
Pour 1/4 cup marinade over lamb.
Roast at 325° approximately 25 minutes per pound.
Baste with 1/4 cup marinade every 20 to 30 minutes.
Allow lamb to rest 15 minutes before carving; serve with vegetables.

title: mini quiches
directions: Line cupcake tins with pie crust.
Saute onion in frypan with margarine.
Remove from pan and cool.
Sprinkle a little of bacon, cheese and onion in each cupcake tin.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add half and half, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour this into cups over bacon/cheese mixture.

title: curried chicken turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients except pie crusts. Allow pie crusts to stand at room temperature for 15 minutes to soften. Unfold each pie crust as directed on package. Remove plastic sheets; press out fold lines. Cut seven 3 1/2 inch circles from each pie crust.

Place about 1 Tbsp. chicken mixture in center of each circle. Brush edge of each circle with water; fold circle in half over filling. Press edges with fork to seal. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 18 to 23 minutes or until light golden brown. Serve warm. If you'd like to serve with a dip, mix 2/3 c. sour cream with 1/3 c. chutney.

title: sugar cure for meat(pork)
directions: Mix ingredients together; this will cover 1 average piece of meat.
Lay on brown paper to apply.
Wrap it up in brown paper. Prop hams and shoulders up on shank end so they will drain.
In a few days, apply a little more of the mixture to each piece lightly.
Wrap well with brown paper.
Place in muslin bags and hang up.
Hang hams and shoulders with shank side down.
Meat should be thoroughly cold and hung in a cold place.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine salt and 1 1/2 tablespoons flour; coat meat with mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet; brown meat slowly on all sides.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; saute until onion is barely tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to skillet; when melted, blend in 1/4 cup flour.
Remove from heat.
Add tomato sauce; gradually add beef stock.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Reduce heat to very low; return meat and mushrooms to skillet and heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; do not boil.
Serve over hot buttered noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool and pick off the bones. Melt margarine and add stuffing mix.
Put almost half in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix chicken, broth and soups together.
Then pour mix into casserole dish.
Put remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: old-time fudge
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 2 quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup and a dash of salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Continue cooking to 234° stirring only as needed to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat; add butter or margarine but do not stir.
Cool to lukewarm for 35 to 40 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat for 7 to 10 minutes or until thick and loses gloss. Spread in buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cut into squares. Yields approximately 1 1/4 pounds.

title: russell's linguine and shrimp
directions: Saute onion, garlic and shrimp in oleo until shrimp are done. Add wine.
Add cooked linguine and toss until hot.
Add steamed spinach, tomato, mushrooms and basil.
Toss to heat through.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: ham with mustard glaze
directions: Place ham, fat side up, on a rack in shallow pan.
Do not cover or add water.
Score ham fat in diamonds (about 1/4-inch deep).
Roast in slow 325° oven for 4 to 6 hours according to size.

title: mexican coleslaw
directions: Pour Zesty Italian dressing over all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: butter cookie thins
directions: In a food processor or with electric mixer, press or beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add egg yolk.
Gradually add flour and dash of salt; blend until smooth.
In a small bowl, combine superfine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of a moistened glass in sugar mixture and press cookies to flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° until edges are slightly golden, about 8 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: lou's custard pie
directions: Scald milk. Add sugar, flavorings and salt.
Mix together. Stir slowly into beaten eggs. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tofu egg salad
directions: Mash tofu until crumbly.
Add rest of ingredients except vegetables.
Mix well and then add vegetables.
Eat like salad or may be used as spread.

title: grape-nuts dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk as directed on box.
Soak Grape-Nuts in 1/4 cup warm water and then let cool.
Add pudding and Grape-Nuts, Cool Whip and marshmallows and put in refrigerator.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat cake mix, water and eggs on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Insert wooden stick 1 1/2 inches into edge of dough.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Frost and decorate.

title: coppenbarger's cheese patties
directions: Cream oleo and cheese together.
Add flour, Rice Krispies, garlic salt and red pepper.
Mix together well.
Make marble-size balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Press flat with fork and bake at 375° until light brown.
These freeze well.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars; beat in peanut butter, egg and vanilla.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions and keep hot. Wash, shell and devein the shrimp.
Pat dry.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and butter.
Saute onion and garlic 5 minutes. Stir in wine, lemon juice, parsley and shrimp.
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Serve over hot drained linguini.

title: ten minute chili
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, crumble ground beef.
Cook, covered on high 3 to 5 minutes, until no longer pink.
Discard drippings.
Stir in beans, vegetables and chili powder.
Cook, covered 6 to 9 minutes until hot.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Soak yeast in water.
Mix dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Add yeast, egg and buttermilk and mix well. Put in greased bowl and refrigerate.
Roll out on well-floured board and cut biscuits.
(The dough will be very sticky.)
Let rise. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Will keep in covered bowl for 1 week in the refrigerator.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Fry bacon until crisp, then drain and cut into small pieces.
Beat eggs lightly; add milk and seasonings.
Use 1 cup milk if the pastry shell is large.
Pour into shell.
Jiggle pan to settle liquid.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes longer or until custard sets.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken lecretici
directions: Dip chicken in flour and chili powder.
Brown in margarine and place in baking dish.
Make roux in skillet.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Drain corn well.
Combine corn, milk, 3/4 cup cheese, eggs, onion and dash of pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Sprinkle over corn.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon chicken and vegetables(diabetic)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Omit salt; drain and set aside. Spray grid with nonstick cooking spray. Prepare coals for grilling. Place chicken, bell peppers and squash on grill for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool and cut into 1-inch pieces. Combine parsley, garlic, lemon peel, salt and black pepper in bowl. Toss chicken, vegetables and pasta. Makes 8 servings.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Blend in baking powder and salt.
Stir in bananas and the 3/4 cup coconut.
Blend in flour.
Turn into greased 14 x 9-inch pan.

title: marge and lou's anniversary whiskey balls
directions: Grind cookies finely between waxed paper or in food processor.	Add all ingredients, mix and set aside in refrigerator for at least 15 minutes.
Form balls, drop into confectioners sugar.
Makes 2-1/2 dozen 3/4 inch balls.

title: creamy herbed chicken
directions: Brown the chicken in oil over medium-high heat. Add onion and saute until onion is soft. Add peas, mushrooms and garlic powder. Stir. Add broth and cream cheese. Simmer, stirring often, until cream cheese is melted and heated through. Cook egg noodles according to directions; drain. Toss with chicken mixture and serve.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Use scant teaspoon per cup of hot water.
Store in baby food size container.
Makes wonderful gifts.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve on crackers.

title: corn bread dressing with pecans and apricots
directions: Saute pecans in butter until crisp, about 2 minutes.
Add onion, celery and apricots; cook until soft, about 10 minutes. Stir in parsley.
Remove from heat and mix with corn bread, wheat bread, sage, pepper and stock.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: mexican dish(quick fix)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch pie plate, layer following in order listed:
Fritos on bottom of dish, then then the shredded lettuce, mixed with chopped green onions.
Top with chili.
Heat this in oven about 15 minutes, then top with more Fritos, shredded cheese and olives.
Return to oven.
Continue heating until cheese melts and Fritos are crisp and golden.
Serve immediately.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients about 20 minutes or until tender. Mash some of the potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until thoroughly heated.
Be sure and keep stirred to protect from scorching.
Remove from heat.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and garlic in blender.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice to taste.
Then add crumbled cheese, mixing only slightly after adding cheese.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Combine cottage cheese and jello.
Then mix in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Chill until it forms a mold.

title: potato pizza casserole
directions: Spread potato slices in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Brown hamburger in skillet with onion.
Mix milk and soup; add cooked meat and pour over potatoes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, soup and milk.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Top rice mixture with chicken breasts.
Sprinkle chicken with French onion soup mix.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer or until brown.

title: barbecued crabs
directions: Salt the inside of each crab.
Soak in sauce for 3 to 4 minutes.
Fry in grease.
Makes enough sauce for 3 1/2 dozen crabs.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roast nuts and cool.
Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together with fork.
Roll in form of ball.
Place in refrigerator for 10 minutes and roll in nuts.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Return sausage to pan and add other ingredients.
Mix well until cheese melts.
Spread on bread (can be frozen at this point).
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour and soda.
Add chips.

title: fire-and-ice tomatoes
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, potato chips and nuts.
Chill dough for several hours.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Put on baking sheet, 2 inches apart.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass covered with damp cloth dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes (watch closely), until lightly browned.

title: tortilla chicken casserole
directions: Combine onion, soups, sour cream, chillies, chicken and some of cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer torn tortillas in 2 layers.
Add chicken mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Garnish with ripe olives and pimentos.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, combine the egg, milk and oil.
Add flour mixture. Mix well.
Stir into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a cup, combine brown sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon.
Stir together, then sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a 375° oven about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 coffee cake.

title: cocoons
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in sauce pan, cooking over medium heat until butter melt.
Add nuts, coconut and dates cooking over medium heat for 6 minutes stirring steady to keep from scorching.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine milk, pudding and water; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon into individual serving dishes.
Chill thoroughly; garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
May add grapes or any other drained fruits.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Have vanilla wafer rounded side up.
Spread thin layer of vanilla frosting, then put one chocolate mint cookie on, then a thin layer of vanilla frosting.
Color coconut with green food coloring (to make it look like green lettuce), put coconut on next layer, then a vanilla wafer, rounded side up. Put a thin layer of honey, sprinkle sesame seed on top.

title: carberry's pepper steak
directions: Cut flank into thin slices against grain.
Sear meat in frying pan.
Combine last 5 ingredients and add to frying pan; simmer on low flame for 25 minutes, covered.
Add sliced pepper and onion and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch to water; stir. Add and wait 5 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix first 9 ingredients.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into well greased tube pan.
Sprinkle morsels over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and cake tests done.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Fold into flat baking dish.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw 30 minutes before serving.
You can garnish with extra cherries before freezing.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine jello and cake mix in medium bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 8 hours.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips, oats and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack.

title: quick coconut cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat pudding and milk on low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in half of the cool whip and 1/2 to 3/4 cup coconut. Pour into crust.
Spread with remaining cool whip; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add onions, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms; simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and sauce, heating thoroughly.
Place in a large casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix well, shape into balls and mash with fork.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini butter
directions: Cook shredded zucchini until tender with enough water to keep from sticking, 20 minutes.

title: pie crust(two to three crusts)
directions: Add salt to flour and cut in lard or Crisco with pastry cutter or two knives until like small peas.
Sprinkle water on and stir with fork gently until ball forms.
Divide and turn out on lightly floured board.
Roll out.
If crust is to be baked before filling, prick generously with fork and bake in preheated 425° oven for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Arrange broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Place cooked chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and spread over chicken layer. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix; leave in fridge overnight or mix in the morning and let set all day in refrigerator.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Put a thin layer of dressing on bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut up half of chicken on that.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1 cup of broth.
Pour over chicken and dressing.
Put another layer of dressing and chicken.
Dilute chicken soup with 1 cup broth.
Pour over chicken and dressing.
Top with remaining dressing and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to form ball stage.
Just before syrup reaches ball stage, beat egg white until stiff, not dry.
Pour about 1/2 of the syrup slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remainder of syrup to soft ball stage or until small amount of syrup forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Add syrup slowly to mixture.
Continue beating until mixture stiffens.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended. Knead lightly.
Roll very thin.
Cut in strips.
If more broth is needed, add milk and a little butter.

title: java chicken
directions: In a small brown bag, combine flour, pepper and salt.
Coat chicken pieces, one at a time, by shaking in the bag.
Fold the top of the bag to contain the flour mixture while shaking. Reserve remaining flour mixture.

title: spring salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-Os in 2 cups of hot water, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: brochetta with salsa
directions: Dice tomatoes.
Set aside.
In a bowl, crush garlic.
Add salt, pepper and vinegar and stir.
Add olive oil and blend.
Add basil.
Drain off excess liquid from tomatoes.
Pour dressing over tomatoes and blend together.
Slice bread.
Place tomato mixture on bread halves.
Grill on the barbecue or place under the oven broiler.

title: bourbon pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blanch pecans for one minute in boiling water.
Drain.
Combine the reduced bourbon, sugar, bitters, Worcestershire sauce and corn oil.
While hot, toss nuts with bourbon mixture.
Let stand ten minutes, then spread on cookie tray.
Bake 30 to 50 minutes, stirring every ten minutes.
When nuts are crisp and lightly brown and liquid has evaporated, turn nuts into bowl.
Combine cayenne, salt, pepper and cumin. Sprinkle over nuts while tossing.
Turn out onto sheet pan to cool in single layer.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate and oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix flour, oats, sugar and margarine.
Reserving 1/2 cup oat mixture, press remainder into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crust.
Top with walnuts, chips and reserved oat mixture.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Spread slices of bread with margarine.
Sprinkle with minced garlic or garlic powder and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Pound chicken
breasts	flat.
Place
a
slice of Swiss cheese on the
chicken
and
then a piece of ham on top.
Roll each one up	and
secure with toothpicks.
Roll this in melted butter and then in bread crumbs.
Place them on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice tenderloin tips into very thin strips.
Reduce white wine and vinegar by boiling for several minutes.
Add to brown gravy. Add this sauce slowly to sour cream, stirring constantly, to prevent curdling.
Add butter (not melted).
Saute tenderloin strips in heavy skillet until light brown.
Strain all grease. Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add to beef.
Add sauce, salt and pepper.
Keep warm.
Serve over steamed rice, noodles or spaetzle. Serves 4.

title: broiled stuffed tomato
directions: Combine bread crumbs and grated cheese together.
Fill tomato halves with bread crumb mixture.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Broil in oven for about 5 minutes.
May need to cut off broiler and bake about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Press into 2 loaf pans lined with foil.
Stor in refrigerator tightly covered.
Slice thinly.

title: honey cornmeal biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients until dough forms. Beat 30 seconds. Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix. Gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Shape into balls.
Knead 10 times. Roll out until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown (8 to 10 minutes). Serve with Honey-Butter.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased iron skillet at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Lard a rectangular pan with part of margarine.
Dump into pan the pie filling and pineapple chunks, distributing evenly.
Cover with cake mix.
Again, spread with nuts and coconut.
Spread sliced butter over ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Stir in butter until melted. Add cheese and eggs. Press into well buttered 10-inch pie pan or 2-quart casserole. Press along the bottom and sides to form the "crust." Add cottage cheese, if desired. Brown ground beef and add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into spaghetti crust and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased baking pan (8x12x2) with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all.
Bake at 275 for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan.
Add green pepper and onion; cook until tender.
Stir in chicken with rice soup, tomato soup and water or beef stock.
Heat to boiling; then turn down heat.
While sauce cooks, make meat balls.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine raw peanuts, sugar, Karo syrup and salt in a 4-cup Pyrex dish or measuring cup.
Stir well.
Cook on Full power for 4 minutes; stir.
Cook 3 1/2 to 4 more minutes on Full power; stir. Add butter and vanilla; cook another 30 seconds to 1 minute on Full power.
Remove and add soda; stir.
Mixture will be foamy. Immediately pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Allow to cool; break into pieces.

title: meringue chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add pinch of salt.
Slowly beat in sugar, chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Put foil on cookie sheet and drop with teaspoon.
Turn oven off and leave in for 2 to 3 hours.

title: 1-2-3- fruit dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boiling on medium, constantly stirring, 1 minute. Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: wilted spinach penne
directions: *If using frozen, use at least one 10-ounce box; defrost and squeeze out well.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Wash thoroughly and place in electric skillet.
Pour Coca-Cola and catsup over chicken.
Cover (leave vent open).
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine ingredients and heat in microwave until melted.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with cut apple slices.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Combine scalded sour cream, sugar, butter and salt; mix well and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; stir in sour cream mixture, then eggs.
Gradually stir in flour (dough will be soft).
Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: german chocolate fudge
directions: Line a 9 x 13 inch baking pan with aluminum foil, extending foil over two sides of pan; spray foil with cooking spray.
Combine chocolate and sweetened condensed milk in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on high power (100%) 2 minutes or until chocolate softens, stirring after each minute.
Stir mixture until chocolate melts.
Stir in pecans, coconut, and vanilla.
Spread mixture into prepared pan.
Cover and chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in an airtight container in a cool place. Yield:
Approximately 8 dozen pieces fudge.

title: kids can do - raggedy robins
directions: Put saucepan on range burner and add cocoa, margarine and milk; stir to blend.
Turn range burner to medium heat, continue stirring and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove saucepan from heat and quickly stir in vanilla extract, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Make sure all ingredients are well blended.
Working quickly, drop mixture onto waxed paper by the teaspoon.
Cool 15 minutes.
Store completely cooled Raggedy Robins in an airtight container.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Put all in bowl and whip at high speed until smooth.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet, break up with fork.
Drain. Spoon sausage into large bowl.
Cool.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Mix with fork.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Good for snacks at parties!

title: garlic-artichoke bread
directions: Chop artichokes and set aside marinade.
On floured board, roll dough into 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Let rest 5 minutes. Brush half of the marinade over the dough.
Sprinkle with artichokes, 1 cup cheese, garlic, basil and oregano.
From long end, roll dough into a snug log. Pinch seam to seal. Brush log with marinade. Lightly cover with plastic wrap and set in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer. Slice thinly when cooled. Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, break cake into little pieces.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add frozen strawberries until dissolved. Pour over cake and jell until sets.
Prepare pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk; fold whipped topping into pudding.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese twist
directions: In skillet, cook green pepper and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in sauce, water, oregano and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add cheese cubes.
Stir just to mix.
Serve over hot macaroni that's been cooked and drained.

title: rosettes
directions: Beat all together in small mixing bowl.
Heat grease in pan. Let rosette iron also heat while the grease is heating. When iron is hot, dip hot iron in dough to top of iron and dip into hot grease for about 5 seconds.
Rosette should come off iron (if it doesn't you can work off with a fork).
Let brown just a little, then turn over for a couple of seconds and take out of pan.
Let cool on paper towel.
You can sprinkle with sugar, powdered sugar or just eat plain.

title: summer sausage dunk
directions: Peel off wrapper from summer sausage. Cut into bite size chunks.
Place in pot.
Pour duck sauce over to cover. Cook over medium heat until hot. Serve warm. Serve with toothpicks.
Fast, easy and delicious!

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Beat together eggs and skim milk.

title: savory onion bread pudding
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a skillet and saut onions. Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer sliced mushrooms on bottom, sauteed onions on top of mushrooms, cheese next and bread on top. Mix soup, milk and soy sauce in a small bowl; pour over top of layered dish. Sprinkle lightly with pepper. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: sundae pie
directions: Stir slightly soft ice cream until smooth, spoon ice cream into pie crust and cover with the pie pan cover lid.
Place in freezer for 3 hours or until hard.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and add pineapple.
Let chill until it begins to set, then add whipped cream to which 1/3 cup sugar has been added.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Cool.
Add chopped onions, chopped bell pepper, chopped artichoke hearts and chopped chicken.
Add marinade from artichoke hearts.
Mix well; chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
You can add more chicken and have a nice luncheon salad.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: Drain cocktail.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add all ingredients but coconut.
Spread in greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sandy jo's summer seafood pasta
directions: *If you're in a hurry, just buy seafood salad.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Stir good.
Boil for 24 minutes. After boiling mix 2 packages Sure-Jell.
Bring back to boil.
Pour into jelly jars.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Add water and mayonnaise; stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with hot fudge sauce.

title: shamrock stew
directions: Cut meat and unpeeled potatoes into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Dredge meat in flour seasoned with garlic, salt and pepper.
Brown in frying pan and arrange in bottom of large casserole.
Add a layer of potatoes and then sliced carrots.
Slice onions and brown with cabbage.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Add bouillon and cover dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Stir after first hour or baking.
Stir again after second hour and continue baking, uncovered.
Stir every half hour during final baking time.

title: orange beets(makes 12 servings)
directions: Drain beets, reserve liquid.
Combine cornstarch and sugar in a saucepan.
Blend in orange juice concentrate, then 6 ounces beet liquid and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add butter and beets.
Reheat and serve or place in double boiler over simmering water to keep hot until serving time.

title: aunt myra's meat loaf
directions: Crush enough crackers to bind ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together.
With hands, form into 2 to 3 loaves.
Add a bit of water to bake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry hot sausage, drain and cool. Spray a large 10 x 10-inch or larger Corning Ware casserole dish with Pam.
Butter bread on both sides and cube.
Cover bottom of dish with bread. Crumble sausage over bread.
Spread on mushrooms. Put cheese on next. Beat eggs, half and half, salt and pepper. I use a whisk. Pour over all other ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate overnight or up to 3 days before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: celery salad
directions: Cut
celery in bite sizes.
Chop onion and soak both in salted water
for
several hours.
Then rinse and drain.
Put into
a bowl and add the remaining ingredients.
You will have to taste to
determine
whether or not it appears to have the flavor you want.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch square metal pan or 10-inch cast-iron skillet; place in hot oven.
Combine cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, sour cream and oil; blend well. Stir in corn.
Pour 1/2 of batter into heated pan.
Cover with cheese.
Spoon remaining batter on top; sprinkle top with chili powder.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cut in squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook fish in water until it flakes.
Remove fish and boil potatoes, salt and onion until tender.
Add fish, milk and half and half.
Heat through.
Add butter and pepper to taste.
Enjoy!

title: lee's caramel popcorn
directions: Cook on medium heat, the sugar, margarine, syrup and salt until boils, stirring.
Cook 5 minutes without stirring.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts and coat well.
Place in shallow pans and cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 250°, stirring occasionally.
Store in covered containers.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Bake graham cracker crust. Melt marshmallows in top of double boiler with 1/2 cup milk.
Add candy bar, reserving 2 squares. Heat until chocolate is melted; blend.
Cool 20 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fill crust.
Shave remaining 2 squares of chocolate over pie.
Chill.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare graham cracker crumb crust according to graham cracker crumb box.
Prepare 1 envelope of Dream Whip according to package. Add softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix with mixer until smooth, then pour over cool crust.
Chill for at least 4 to 5 hours.
Before serving pour cherry pie filling over dessert.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onions. Add zucchini; saute. Cook macaroni in salted water. Mix with zucchini, onions and ham. Put in ovenproof dish. Mix yogurt and egg; spread over noodles. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Serves 4 hungry kids and 2 adults.

title: easy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deadly bread
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add mustard, minced onion, lemon juice and poppy seed.
Simmer until onions are soft.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in cream and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; continue to beat until smooth.
Mix brown sugar, graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and ground almonds together and coat bottom and sides of 9-inch spring pan. Pour in cream cheese mixture and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Separate cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Add other vegetables.

title: chocolate slush
directions: Mix well flour, margarine and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Put on crust when cool.
Beat chocolate pudding as directed and pour over cream cheese layer. Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Soak overnight in 1 cup salt.
Add to enough water to cover vegetables.
Bring to boil in solution.
While hot, drain well. Simmer together pickles and sauce, just until hot.
Put into jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook vegetables.
Mix Stove Top dressing and dry ingredients together and pour over top of vegetables.
Melt margarine and pour over top of ingredients.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Roll chicken pieces to cover the bottom of glass dish.
Mix soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with layer of cheese slices.
Pour dry stuffing mix over top.
Drizzle melted butter and water over dry stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: In mixing
bowl,
add
butter
(cut
in pieces), sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook
on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until all is melted.
Add
nuts	and
vanilla.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and chill.	Cut into squares.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain.
Blend well with remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into buttered shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Scald the rice.
Scald the cabbage until leaves will roll without breaking.
Take leaves apart.
When rice is cool, mix in ground chuck, seasoning salt, pepper and bacon fat or butter.
Put rice and ground chuck mixture in cabbage leaves and roll tight enough to hold mixture.
Put in cooking pot and add tomato sauce and water, enough to cover them.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: meatball cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; beat together.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Dough will become too thick to mix with electric mixer, continue mixing by hand until well blended.)
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tenderloin salad
directions: Marinate mushrooms, onions and artichokes in dressing.
Drain and reserve dressing.
In a large glass bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, marinated vegetables and meat.
Make two layers, ending with meat.
Pour reserved dressing over all.
This may be prepared ahead. Serve with cheese souffle and French bread.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Combine milk, marshmallows and orange juice in top of double boiler, let marshmallows melt.
Blend cracker crumbs and spices in large bowl.
Then add raisins, dates, nuts and candied fruit.
Stir in mixture of marshmallows with large spoon and hand until all crumbs are moistened.
Then pack tightly in greased pan and store in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
Run knife around pan and take cake out.
Wrap in wax paper, then in foil and store.

title: after school gingersnaps
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, sugars, egg and molasses.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and rinse macaroni.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: stuffed potatoes(patate ripieni)
directions: From my cousin, Carmi.

title: cheese whiz casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 2-quart ungreased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. marvin's magic muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix the flour and mayonnaise in a mixing bowl.
Add milk, a small amount at a time, stirring only until dry particles are moistened. Grease a 6-cup muffin tin and spoon in the mixture. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and shape into balls and roll into flour.
Brown in oil.
Remove meatballs.

title: freezer ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually and beat until stiff.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Add half and half (or whipping cream and half and half).
Put in electric or hand-crank freezer and add milk up to the fill mark on the freezer.
Freeze 20 minutes.
This is a creamy, good vanilla ice cream.
Not for those watching their cholesterol, though!

title: orange tapioca
directions: Put water, sugar and tapioca in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add frozen orange juice.
When cool, add oranges and peaches.
Refrigerate and serve with whipped topping.

title: neiman-marcus delight cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on the box.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle on bottom of pan the pecans, coconut and cherries.
Pour cake mix batter over this. Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Cream together well and drop by spoonfuls on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put hamburger in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken soup, milk, salt, pepper and onion.
Stir well and pour over hamburger. Place Tater Tots on top, still frozen.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: california casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender-crisp.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Slice cheese and arrange on top.
Mix crackers with melted butter; place over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: beetnick cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add blended beets.
Mix at medium speed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and 1/2 pound melted butter together until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs; mix thoroughly.
Press firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and chocolate bits.
Spread evenly over top.
Let set in refrigerator for a few hours.

title: chicken breasts romana
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Lightly brown in oil. Remove chicken and set aside.
Add ham, onion, celery and basil to oil; simmer and stir for 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Add stock or water to tomato paste.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 40 to 60 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add parsley.
Serve with boiled spaghetti, swirled with a long-tined kitchen fork into individual portions.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine the peppers and onion.
Bring the vinegar to boiling point, add the sugar and salt.
Pour over the vegetables. Let stand 2-3 hours before serving. Store in a tightly covered jar in refrigerator.
This relish will keep for about a week.

title: vegetable chicken stir-fry
directions: Prepare all vegetables.
Heat oil in wok or large frying pan on high.
Add chicken and saute, stirring frequently.
When chicken is lightly browned, add onion and celery.
Saute, stirring frequently.
Continue to add remaining vegetables, stirring frequently.
When vegetables are almost done, add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to medium-high, cover and continue to cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes, depending on degree of doneness desired.
Serve immediately over rice with soy sauce.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend ingredients in a Cuisinart until a ball forms. Wrap in plastic wrap and place in refrigerator until filling is made. Once out of fridge, roll out dough and cut into 3-inch round shapes. Place each round in a well-greased cupcake pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix in coconut and oats until well blended.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
In a small skillet, melt margarine.
Add green peppers and onions. Save until crisp-tender.
In a large bowl, combine cream-style corn, whole kernel corn, eggs and corn muffin mix; blend well. Add onion mixture, mix well and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until firm and set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving, approximately 12 cup serving.

title: taco salad(great for pot luck dinners!!)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add cheese, onion, tomatoes, lettuce and nacho cheese Doritos.
Pour the Catalina dressing over the ingredients and mix or toss as in a salad.
Ready to serve warm or cold.

title: endive salad
directions: Crisp endive in ice water about 15 minutes before using. Drain; gently dry in paper towels.
Cut endive heads in halves lengthwise, starting at root ends.
Combine remaining ingredients except chives; mix well.
Spoon dressing over endive; sprinkle chopped chives on top.
Serves 6.

title: doris' jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill.
Mash cream cheese with vinegar until smooth. Add pineapple and juice; blend well.
Add nuts.
Chill.
Combine two mixtures when jello mixture begins to thicken.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into desired mold and chill.

title: layered jello
directions: Follow steps 1 and 2 for each flavor (lemon is a good starting flavor).
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan (can use mayonnaise in place of shortening in pan).

title: uncle mark's punch
directions: Add water to juices per directions.
Mix ingredients.
Add sugar if desired.
Let stand.
Add ginger ale as you see fit.
Add Ice to cool.

title: shirl's graham cracker pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Crush crackers and mix with butter in a 9-inch pie plate.
Pat bottom and sides to form a crust.
In a medium bowl, combine milk, juice and grated rind of the lemons. Beat egg yolks and stir into the milk mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture.
Pour into the shell and bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger stroganoff(bison)
directions: Saute onion and add meat. Cook until done. Add flour and cook 5 minutes. Add soup. Simmer 10 minutes. Add sour cream and heat. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put chicken pieces on top.
Bake at 300°
for 2 hours or until done (uncovered).

title: cabbage roll
directions: Heat cabbage until tender.
Combine next seven ingredients; make into balls.
Peel off cabbage leaves and wrap around balls. Place in loaf pan.
Cover with Ragu sauce, sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover with foil, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover, bake 30 minutes longer.
Can add cheese to top.

title: creamy turkey soup
directions: In a large kettle, saute onion and celery in butter until tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in flour and seasonings; gradually add milk, stirring until thickened. Add turkey, carrots and enough broth until soup is desired consistency. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Add peas; cover and simmer another 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla delight
directions: Crush crackers and blend in melted butter to make crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Chill crust while mixing pudding mix, milk and softened ice cream. Spread over crust.
Chill until partly firm and cover with Cool Whip.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: coconut peach shortcake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add coconut; cut in shortening until fine.
Add milk all at once.
Spread dough into greased 9-inch layer pan.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Split and butter layers if desired.
Put half the peaches on bottom layer.
Place other half on top and spread remaining peaches over it.
Garnish with whipped cream and coconut.

title: genevieve's cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll out.
Cut into cookies with cutter that has a ruffled or scalloped edge.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle chopped nuts on them.
Bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat.
Mix container of cottage cheese with Mozzarella cheese.
Add the meat to the cheese mixture.
Stuff uncooked shells with beef and cheese; place shells in pan.
Add 1 cup of water to bottom of pan to soften shells as they cook.
Pour sauce of the shells.
You may add the extra beef and cheese if any is leftover.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes or until shells are soft at 425°.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, place raisins and cover with warm tap water. Allow to plump up as you prepare the dough.
Add flour, baking powder, sugar, cinnamon and salt into a medium bowl.
Mix with a whisk or fork.
Add shortening into the flour mixture.
Cut shortening and flour mixture together until crumbly.
Do not over mix this stage.
Add milk and stir.
Squeeze the raisins dry and add to dough.
Mix in kneading about 10-12 times.
Cut into biscuits and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Top with icing.

title: easy tortellini soup
directions: Combine green onion and vegetable broth in a 5-quart saucepan. Bring to boiling over high heat.
Gradually stir the tortellini into the broth; reduce the heat to medium high.
Cook 3 minutes; gradually stir in the pea pods and cook an additional 3 minutes. Stir in pesto sauce and serve.
Nutrient value per serving:
355 calories. 15 g. protein. 15 g. fat., 40 g. CHO, 1,485 mg. sodium, 36 mg. cholesterol.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter. Mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pie pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine butter, bread and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown and firm. Serve with Bourbon Sauce.

title: macabeef
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
While macaroni is cooking, cook ground beef and drain.
Drain macaroni when finished.
Combine all ingredients in microwavable dish with lid; leave some cheese and sprinkle oregano on top.
Microwave until hot.
Serve with garlic bread and fresh tossed salad.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Mix together and put into unbaked pie crust and bake for 1 hour at 400° for about 10 minutes, then turn down to 300° for rest of the hour.
Knife comes out clean when done, like a custard.

title: hamburger rice
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: the best pancakes
directions: In large bowl, beat together 2 tablespoons oil, 1 egg and 1 cup milk.
Sift together 1 cup all-purpose flour, 2 tablespoons baking powder, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients, blending well.
Stir in 1 additional tablespoon milk.
Fry on lightly oiled hot griddle.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place fruit in greased baking dish. Combine dry ingredients. Add melted margarine, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm or cold with your favorite whipped topping.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Put into a large pan.
Add tomatoes, water, spaghetti sauce and macaroni.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Add cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.
Reheats well, also freezes.

title: chicken and peas pilau
directions: Saute onions and rice in margarine until onions are transparent.
Stir in broth, peas and chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and saffron.
Bring to a boil.
Stir once or twice.
Lower heat to simmer.
Cover.
Cook 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding by directions on package.
Add sugar and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over bananas and garnish with vanilla wafers.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, cook sun-dried tomato pesto, stirring, 2 minutes or until fragrant.
Add shrimp and chopped garlic; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly or until shrimp turns opaque and is just cooked through.
Stir in salt, ground black pepper and lemon juice until blended.
Serve shrimp and sauce over warmed rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers fine.
Cut rest of ingredients with scissors and mix well by hand.
Put waxed paper in pan and pack mixture into pan.
Put weight on top to press.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Brown chops in butter.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Layer chops in baking dish.
Cover with stewed tomatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk butter pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, stir together butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Press mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chunks on crust. Let stand until softened, about 5 minutes.
Spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Yields about 36 bars.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry onions and peppers in margarine.
Add ground beef and sausage.
Fry until no longer red.
Cook noodles 15 minutes or until tender.
Mix all ingredients with sauces.
Put in a casserole dish and top with pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until bubbly or until cheese is melted.

title: polly's vegetable soup
directions: Bring tomato juice to boil.
Add vegetables; stir and cook for a while.
Add crumbled hamburger and continue cooking, stirring to prevent sticking.
Add salt and sugar to taste.
Serve.
This makes a large amount but also can be canned for later use.

title: pesto
directions: Blend 1st five ingredients until you have a smooth paste.
Add more olive oil, if needed.
Stir in cheese.
Serve or store in refrigerator for up to ten days or freeze for three months.

title: pepper steak
directions: In 2-quart Farberware mixing bowl, marinate steak at least 10 minutes with sherry, soy sauce, cornstarch and salt.
Set aside. In Farberware electric wok, add 2 tablespoons of the oil.
Set heat control dial at 350°.
When the light goes out, add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Stir-fry until pepper is tender-crisp.
Remove to 1-quart Farberware mixing bowl.
To wok, add remaining tablespoon of oil and steak mixture.
Stir-fry until steak is cooked.
Add green pepper mixture and stir-fry until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potatoes.
Add potatoes. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel food deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together flour and first amount of sugar.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Add second amount of sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating on high speed until mixture holds stiff peaks.
Gently fold in flavorings.
Sprinkle flour-sugar mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, over mixture, folding in gently just until flour mixture disappears.
Push batter into ungreased tube pan, 10 x 4-inches.
Gently cut through batter.
Bake 35 minutes. Invert tube pan on funnel to cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Combine oil, eggs and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bread crumb noodles
directions: In frypan, melt butter; add bread crumbs and brown, stirring often so as not to burn.
When nicely browned, pour over warm noodles, stirring to coat well.
Not necessary, but additional baking in medium hot oven for a short while does give a nice flavor.
This is good as an accompanying dish for pork chops served with white cream-style corn.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add eggs, water, pumpkin and salad oil.
Mix well and add nuts. Grease and flour loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mazurek(polish bar cookies)
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside.
Mix 1 beaten egg and 3 tablespoons milk.
Add egg mixture to flour mix; stir until moistened (cut in to complete).
Pat evenly into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Beat 1 egg.
Stir in 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Add nuts.
Remove pan from oven.
Spread with lemon mix.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: new england brown bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine whole wheat flour, buttermilk and molasses. Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into well-greased coffee cans, 5 1/4 x 3 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bread tests done.
Yields 2 cans.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together and freeze in a one gallon ice cream freezer.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: 1) Heat oil in pan over medium heat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Remove and set aside. 2) Brown and crumble ground beef. Drain off fat.
Stir in catsup, mustard, salt, and pepper.
Set aside. 3) On floured surface, unroll dough from can of rolls. Press perforations together and roll into 12 inch square.
Place in 9 inch pie plate and trim to 1 inch beyond edge. 4) Spoon meat mixture into dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with onions.
Pour 2 beaten eggs over onion layer. 5) Unroll remaining dough, press perforations together and roll into 11 inch square.
Place on top of onion layer.
Trim & pinch together with bottom dough layer. 6) Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt
butter
or margarine in 8-inch square pan or dish. Make batter
of
sugar,
flour,
baking powder, salt and milk. Pour batter over butter.
Add peaches and juice.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° until dough is brown and fruit is cooked thoroughly, about 50 to 60 minutes.
(Yellow food coloring for a richer looking batter may be used.)

title: "quick" cajun rice dressing
directions: Cook ground meat in skillet with chopped onion and bell pepper.
Drain, then add 2 packages Cajun rice (Lipton brand). Follow directions on package.
Put in large casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes.
Then serve.

title: crab rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on toast or crackers.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Mix room temperature cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip and pour over crust.
Mix jello and boiling water, then add thawed strawberries.
Refrigerate until partially set, about 1 to 2 hours.
Serve.

title: wassetti
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in butter or oil until soft.
Brown meat.
Add sauteed onion and pepper.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Place in sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover mixture with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick mix with milk; add grated cheese.
Mix 30 seconds to soft mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet, ungreased.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown at 425°.
Mix melted butter and garlic powder, brush on top of biscuit before removing from pan.

title: christmas eve pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Add pecans and stir gently until coated.
Set aside.

title: macaroni slaw salad
directions: Toss together and cover; chill several hours.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls in a pan.
Brown and drain sausage. Spread sausage over rolls.
Add hash browns and cheese.
Stir egg in milk; pour over mixture.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes, until rolls are brown.

title: tahitian punch
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together juices and soda.
Spoon sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately.
Makes 38 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Cut oranges in thirds.
Beat first 3 ingredients together. Fold in orange pieces.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes and put in buttered baking dish.
Put in half of potatoes, 1/2 butter, flour and salt.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add onion, tomatoes and chili powder.
Cook 1/2 hour. Add pinto or kidney beans about 1/2 hour before eating.

title: black bean and corn salsa
directions: Mix all and refrigerate until ready to use. Serve with corn chips or over grilled chicken.

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and baking soda; mix well.
Cover, chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press into 1/2 inch thick circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Remove and cool completely.
Melt chocolate pieces, stir in vegetable shortening, mixing until smooth.
Top each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. Chill until set.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: kansas baked beans
directions: Season	with
brown sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Bake
at	least
one hour at 350° or all day in crock-pot.

title: laura's "i don't feel like cooking" meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil or applesauce, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins, pineapple and nuts.
Blend.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or two greased and floured bread pans for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: glory bee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add oil and baby fruit.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix 4 minutes.
Add pecans. Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 300° in Bundt pan.

title: bertha's chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Put baking soda into buttermilk and stir.
Add this to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and cocoa together and add this together, mixing well.
Put in boiling water and vanilla last.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put your favorite chocolate icing on top.

title: crock pot chili
directions: Combine all ingredients except beans, lemon juice and parsley in crock pot.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours.
Add beans, cover and cook on high for 1 hour longer.
Stir in lemon juice and parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: turkey rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour. Add chicken broth gradually.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add pimento, almonds, pepper, turkey and rice. Stir to combine.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add with zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Put in 15
x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350` for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with:

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and both sugars.
Add vanilla, eggs and then dry ingredients.
Add nuts, if desired.
Roll into medium size balls and press down with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° about 12 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening into flour and salt until granular.
Add water, egg and vinegar.
Blend.
Dough is very stiff.
May store in refrigerator for later use.
Makes a flaky crust.
It really never fails.
You will think you are a great southern cook.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Layer ingredients in 10 ounce pie pan.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in oleo until tender.
Cook broccoli. Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Put celery, onion, green pepper and tomatoes and add all seasonings in large pot and cook while sausage is browning, then add sausage and cook for 10 minutes or so.
Stir occasionally.
Add zucchini and simmer covered until vegetables are soft, not crunchy.
Do not let the vegetables get mushy.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: easy caramel orange ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Place teaspoonfuls of orange marmalade in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well; set aside.
Separate biscuits.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in pan, spacing evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake near center of 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown. Cool upright in pan for 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water in saucepan and bring to boil.
Add softened cream cheese and beat until almost dissolved.
Add apricot and pineapple and set aside to thicken.
Whip evaporated milk. Pour jello mixture in milk.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with nuts. Congeal and cut in squares.

title: miracle whip dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place on serving dish.
Chill.
Serve with favorite cracker.

title: rolls(good for freezing)
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening. Mix yeast and warm water.
Add egg white.
Pour into first mixture; stir well.
Let rise until doubled in bulk (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Put out on floured board; knead well.
Cut.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
Package in plastic bag.
Remove desired number each meal and let thaw and rise (about 1 1/2 hours).
Bake in hot oven (425° to 450°) for 20 minutes or until done.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Boil 2 cups V-8 juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot juice; add 2 cups cold V-8 juice and remaining ingredients.

title: apple slump
directions: Combine apples,
sugar,
cinnamon and water.
Cover and bring to a
boil.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder. Add milk to make
a	soft dough.
Drop batter by spoonful into apple mixture.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with vegetable oil spray.
Slice bread into 1/2-inch slices.
Place bread tightly together in one layer in glass pan.
Place eggs in bowl; beat lightly.
Add milk, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla; mix with whisk.
Pour half of the liquid over bread.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Place apples on top of bread to cover bread.
Pour remaining egg mixture over apples.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Dot with butter. Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with maple syrup.
Makes 12 servings.

title: special egg dish(low calorie)
directions: Spray small baking dish with nonstick spray.
Break egg into dish.
Top with ham, cheese and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.
One serving equals 250 calories or 3 medium fat meat and 1/2 fat exchanges.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator.
Can use either pie filling. Good to freeze.

title: italian beef crock-pot
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Salt and pepper slightly.
Pour vinegar and water in.
Chop large onion; place over heat.
Add the garlic, Italian seasoning, anise seed, rosemary and sweet basil. Cook for 8 hours on high setting and for 4 hours on low setting.

title: bierocks (german)
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Add cabbage, onions, salt and pepper.
Add 3 tablespoons water to steam cabbage and onion.
Do not overcook.
Prepare roll mix; roll out to 18-inches.
Cut into 4 sections.
Fill with mixer; seal corners.
Place on baking sheet.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat lightly, stirring.
Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and simmer a few minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage; chop medium fine.
Heat corned beef and salt in medium saucepan to boiling point.
Add cabbage; cover.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water and refrigerate.
Dissolve orange jello in 1 cup hot water, adding to it marshmallows, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, softened cream cheese and nuts.
Chill.

title: ranchburgers
directions: Select corn with fresh, green husks.
Just before cooking, remove husks and silk; cut out any blemishes.
Wrap each ear of corn in a square of waxed paper, twisting ends tightly.
Place in microwave oven with about 1-inch space between ears.
Cook on High power (4 ears for approximately 15 to 18 minutes or until tender). Use caution when unwrapping corn, as they will remain hot for a time after removing from microwave.

title: gefilte fish
directions: Put the fish and onion through a meat grinder.
Place the mixture in a bowl.
Add the other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Do not use all the matzo meal at once because you may not need much in order to make a firm and workable fish paste.
Season generously with salt and pepper.
Form into balls and cook in the fish stock.
Let it come to a boil, then cook slowly for 1 hour with a lid on the kettle.
Serve the fish cold in some of the broth.
Traditionally horseradish is served on the side.
Makes 20.

title: sweet nothings
directions: You will also need one large brown grocery bag.

title: sweet vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, set aside. Slice onions about 1/4 inch thick. Melt butter in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Cover bottom of dish with a layer of onion slices, top with a layer of stuffing mix. Sprinkle one cup of cheese. Repeat layers, reserving about 2 tablespoons of stuffing mix for the top. Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly and lightly browned.

title: family styled mexican pizza
directions: Combine all the ingredients into a medium-sized bowl.
Stir until blended, about 40 to 50 strokes.
Lightly grease the bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch or 12-inch round pizza pan.

title: fresh fruit medley
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve. May top each serving with sour cream, if desired.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, vanilla, sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add flour to mixture and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Spread with butter.
Sprinkle half of dough with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold other half over and cut in 24 strips, 1-inch wide.
Hold strips at both ends and twist.
Place on greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake and glaze.

title: mississippi brunswick stew
directions: Combine
first	6
ingredients in a large Dutch oven or stock pot; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add
chicken and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from broth, reserving
broth
in Dutch oven.
Cool meat;
bone and coarsely chop.
Set aside.

title: chicken salad with a twist
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and cool. Combine next 7 ingredients and beat until creamy. Add to macaroni, stirring well. Stir in chicken, celery, eggs, onions and olives. Chill several hours. Serve on lettuce leaf. Yields 8 generous servings.

title: easy pie dough
directions: Cut flour, salt, sugar and Crisco until well blended, beat egg well.
Add enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix with fork.
Roll out on floured board, also good for cobblers.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jello (2 cups hot water and 2 cups cold water). Pour into 10x14-inch Pyrex pan.
Chill till partly set.
Dissolve lemon Jello in 1 c. hot water in top of double boiler, add marshmallows and stir to melt.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 c. pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat till well blended and stir in pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in chilled cream and mayonnaise.
Chill until thick.
Pour in layer over lime.
Chill until almost set.
Dissolve cherry Jello in 2 cups hot water, add 2 C. cold water.
Chill until syrupy.
Pour over pineapple layer. Chill until firm.
Serves 24.
Very Pretty!!!

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chew cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle white powdered sugar over.
Cut in squares while warm.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "male" caramel cookies
directions: Melt oleo and pour over sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Fold in eggs and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put eggs in a bowl and beat well.
Add sugar, lard, salt, allspice and warm milk.
Add yeast, then flour.
Let rise until double.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise again until about double. Then bake in very hot lard.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugars and butter well.
Add eggs; mix.
Add flour mixtures, oatmeal, vanilla and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° approximately 12 minutes.

title: emma linnea's swedish cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers in thin slices.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and parsley.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour dressing over cucumbers and chill at least 2 hours.
Nice summertime salad.

title: sausage and rice
directions: To use with leftover spaghetti.

title: almond crust cherry cream pie
directions: Make pie crust as usual.
Line pan.
Prick sides and bottom with fork. Add 1/3 cup slivered almonds. Bake until light tan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Press in 6 x 10-inch pan. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Heat juice and cornstarch until thick.
Add pineapple and spread on top.

title: squash potato bake
directions: Peel and cook potatoes with cut-up squash.
When done, drain. Add butter.
Mash together; then bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lite cherry crumb dessert
directions: Melt stick of margarine with box of cake mix.
Pour cherry pie filling into baking pan.
Cover filling with cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash bread
directions: Peel and grate squash.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, allspice, baking powder and cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add oil, squash, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well, then add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Can top with hard lemon sauce or cream cheese frosting.

title: fruit torte
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a slightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350°. Test at 50 minutes.
Bake 60 minutes, if needed.
Add to cover top any fresh fruit.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Cut fish into serving pieces.
Stir salt into milk.
Dip fish in milk, then in breadcrumbs.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Pour melted margarine over fish.
Place in oven 3/4 of the way in oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix fruit punch and lemonade with water according to their directions.
In large container add fruit-ade mixture.
Add ginger ale and serve over ice.

title: apple-dapple cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine flour, coconut and salt.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well (batter will be stiff).
Drop by tablespoonfuls, 1 inch apart, onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack to cool. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small pieces.
Cook until done. Mash.
Add:

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13 pan.
Poke holes in the cake while it is hot and pour over the cake the cream of coconut, milk and pineapple.
Cool cake and spread with Cool Whip and coconut. Refrigerate cake.

title: heart-smart pie crust
directions: Mix in pie pan.
Press around bottom and sides.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: deluxe coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper and onion in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture.
Let stand for several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
This will keep for at least 1 week in refrigerator.

title: sandy's barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix these ingredients together well; form into a loaf.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Dip each eggplant slice in beaten egg, then in breading meal. Fry slices in olive oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: to clarify butter
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter over low heat.
