Remove the pan from the heat, let the butter stand for 3 minutes and skim the froth.
Strain the butter through a sieve lined with a double thickness of rinsed and squeezed cheesecloth into a bowl, leaving the milky solids in the bottom of the pan.
Pour the clarified butter into a jar or crock and store it, covered, in the refrigerator.
The butter keeps, covered and chilled, indefinitely.
When clarified, butter loses about one fourth of its original volume.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breast halves to 1/2-inch thickness.
In a small bowl, combine the mustard mixture evenly over chicken breasts.
Top each breast with a slice of Swiss cheese, then tuck and roll them up.
Dip chicken breast rolls in the beaten eggs, then in the bread crumbs.
Place rolled and coated breasts in a large skillet; saute in butter until golden brown.
Remove breasts from skillet and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for about 25 minutes, until fully cooked.
Yields 12 servings.

title: old fashion cole slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in large bowl. Pour sugar on top and do not stir. In a small sauce pan, combine vegetable oil, vinegar, celery seed, pepper and salt; bring to a boil. Pour hot mixture over cabbage and again, do not stir. Let stand 1 hour, then cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. Stir before serving. This keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet and fry until done, but not hard. Stir occasionally while frying to keep crumbled fine.
Put sausage into a colander and let drain. Cool.

Spray a baking pan, 13 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch, with Pam and unroll the crescent rolls in the pan in 2 strips. Pinch together the middle seam and perforated places. Spread with fingers to cover bottom of pan.

Crumble sausage over the roll crust evenly. Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat eggs, milk, salt and oregano together and pour this egg mixture as evenly as possible over the cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let pizza set for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: pearl's gooey butter cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, pour dry yellow cake mix.
Melt butter.
Beat 1 egg in small bowl.
Pour the butter in the bowl with the egg; mix well.
Pour over dry cake mix.
Mix until all cake mix is moist; press into pan.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar, 3 eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
After cooling cake, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: fresh broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop the broccoli, cauliflower and onion.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and break into small pieces; place in a large casserole dish. Add soups and milk and mix together. Sprinkle noodles and almonds on top. Bake until bubbly at 325°.

title: homemade noodles and gravy
directions: Makes 6 cups or 10 ounces of noodles.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with broccoli, celery, carrots, mushrooms, cauliflower and zucchini.

title: orange cloud salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges thoroughly.
Combine Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle in jello and stir.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Especially nice for ladies luncheon.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, then chopped celery, green peppers and onions and the frozen peas.
Keep layering until you reach top of pan.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and put over vegetables.
Top with bacon bits.
Will keep for days in refrigerator.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook onions and peppers until done.
Add tomatoes (if using fresh, quarter and boil in just enough water to cover for approximately 10 minutes).
Add flour slowly, stirring constantly, until thick (you may need to add a little more flour if using fresh tomatoes).
Add milk or water gradually until desired consistency.
Add a little sugar to desired taste.
Pour into dish; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven if desired.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter in a pot and add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Turn off heat and add cereal and stir. Spread evenly in a 9x13 pan and allow to cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
Measure bran flakes and milk into a large bowl.
Stir and let stand 1 or 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Stir in raisins and coconut.
Spoon into greased muffin tin and bake at 350° to 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Pound out chicken cutlets.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on top of each cutlet and roll up tightly, securing with a string. On wax paper, combine flour and pepper and mix.
Roll each cutlet to coat.
In a non-stick skillet, add a small amount of oil.
Add cutlets, turning frequently until brown.
Add to skillet remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer 12 - 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine Mazola, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and chili sauce; store in refrigerator indefinitely.
Wash and clean spinach.
Mix with sliced eggs.
Toss with dressing.
Garnish with bacon and onion rings.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Add thawed potatoes and pour into large 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix topping of 1/4 cup margarine and 2 cups crushed corn flakes. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening, salt and baking powder in large bowl. Mix well with pastry blender or fork.
Lightly beat egg in cup; add vinegar and enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Beat lightly.
Add to dough mixture in parts and mix until blended and ready to roll.
Can refrigerate before rolling if desired.

title: pineapple cake - cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix until moist, then beat 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40
to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook roast by boiling for several hours.
(I usually cook it the day before.
Cooking in the oven dries it out too much.) Shred beef by pulling apart with fingers and removing all fat and bone.
In saucepan, combine enchilada mix, tomato sauce and water; simmer 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup of this mixture to meat along with half of grated cheese.
Heat tortillas until they are soft and warm.
Place 2 tablespoons meat mixture on each tortilla and top with 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Roll each tortilla and place seam side down on nonstick casserole.
Spread remaining sour cream over top and sprinkle with green chiles and remaining cheese.
Finally, spoon enchilada sauce mixture over all.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place diced chicken over broccoli.
Combine remaining ingredients and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Pour over chicken layer. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana-apple cake
directions: Spray glass pan with Pam.
Mix oil, sugar and egg white.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; 106 calories per slice.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Take out 1 cup of mixture and set aside.
Bake rest (2 layers).
In a saucepan, mix pineapple, sugar, margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Add the 1 cup of reserved cake mixture and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly and use to frost cake.
It will cover the top of both layers but not the sides.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Add 1 1/3 cups of coconut after beating. Bake in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan at 350° for about 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.	Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool on rack. Place on serving tray.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream Cheese Icing:
Cream together two 8 ounce packages cream cheese,
1 1/4 cups powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, blending
well.

title: hot dog-potato casserole
directions: In a large pot, place diced potatoes, cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour off 1/2 of the water, add milk to just cover potatoes; bring to boil.
Turn to medium heat.
Add cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
After cheese is completely melted, add cornstarch (mixed with 1/4 cup water).
Stir well to thicken.
Add hot dogs and mix in well on low heat.
After a few minutes, hot dogs should be heated.
Serve hot and add cheese to top, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in order given.
Mix remaining ingredients together; spread over top of salad.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Mix just before serving.

title: pasta salad with broccoli
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, broccoli and onion. In a small bowl, combine salad dressing, milk, dressing mix and salt. Add to pasta mixture; toss to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate for an hour or more. Just before serving, stir in bacon.

title: old english rich christmas cake
directions: Use 8-inch round cake pan.
Brush pan with melted shortening. (The following is how the old original English recipe is written: Cut 2 rounds of waxed paper to fit base of pan.
Put one in bottom, cut a doubled strip of waxed paper 2-inches deeper than the pan and long enough to go around inside.
Make 1-inch fold along the length of the strip and make diagonal snips 1-inch apart to the fold.
Fit the strip around the sides of the pan with the snipped edge fitting neatly on the base.
Cover it with the other round of paper and brush entire lining with melted shortening.)

title: italian stuffed peppers
directions: Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Mix sour cream, Romano cheese, bread crumbs, eggs, salt and garlic powder.
Then mix spinach in.

title: spaghetti chicken dinner
directions: Salt chicken and brown in oil in large skillet.
Drain off drippings.
Combine tomatoes, stock, parsley, garlic
salt and thyme.
Stir.
Blend mushroom liquid into flour; stir into tomato mixture.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes. Cook spaghetti when sauce is just about done.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Break broccoli or cauliflower into small pieces and cook until just tender.
Drain and place in shallow, 2-quart casserole dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; arrange bacon on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oleo or butter.
Pour soup on top of the roast. Sprinkle onion soup mix over roast and bay leaf.
Place in covered pan at 350° for 3 hours.

title: aunt marlene's marvelous squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Add other ingredients, except half the stuffing and margarine.
Mix well; pour into a 2-quart casserole. Melt margarine; mix with remaining stuffing.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly around edges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cut the filet mignon into bite size pieces.
Brown in a skillet with onions and mushrooms.
Add the bouillon cube and water to skillet.
Add the sour cream.
Mix it together.
Add the warm sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Bake crust 3 to 4 minutes. Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour into partially baked crust and place on lowest rack in oven. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna swiss pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Mix together tuna, cheese and green onions and spoon into pie shell.
Mix eggs, mayo and milk together and pour over mixture in shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: slow cooked sauerkraut soup
directions: In a slow cooker, combine first 12 ingredients.
Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours or vegetables are tender.
Garnish in divided series with bacon.

title: heath grahams
directions: Separate grahams and fill a large lipped cookie sheet.
Melt sugar and butter until mixture bubbles (medium heat).
Pour over grahams.
Sprinkle chopped nuts.
Cool for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Separate on aluminum foil immediately.

title: baked french toast
directions: Butter a 9x13

baking dish. Arrange slices of bread in the bottom. In a large bowl beat together eggs, milk, cream, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour over bread slices and refrigerate overnight. The next morning preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a small saucepan combine butter, brown sugar and syrup, heat until bubbly. Pour over egg mixture. Bake uncovered for 40 minutes.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Cook egg noodles as directed. Melt Velveeta a little at a time in Ro-Tel and soup mixture. Pour meat, noodles and soup and cheese mixture together.
Rolls and green salad top this meal.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Blend in blender for 30 seconds on high.
Serve in tall glass.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook mushrooms 1 hour or until done.
Take stems off mushrooms.
Stuff mushrooms with mix and top with 3 slices of swiss cheese.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs and blend in buttermilk.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Mix in oil, bran flakes, nuts and dates.
Allow batter to sit, covered, for 24 hours.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.
Prepare desired number of muffin tins with Baker's Joy or paper wrappers.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain. Toss spaghetti with butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread 4 ounces sliced mushrooms over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cowhands casserole
directions: Cook and brown first 3 ingredients; drain.
Put layer of hamburger on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then put 1 small jar Picante sauce.
Next, layer corn with juice, then Ranch Style beans and cheese.
Finally, make corn bread mix as package directs and pour over cheese.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ron's orange salad(italy)
directions: Section oranges into bowl.
Mix olive oil, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic.
Pour over oranges and toss until sections are completely coated.
Let set in refrigerator for a short time before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham and swiss roll-ups
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Spread half of cream cheese mixture evenly on ham slices; top with cheese slices.
Spread remaining mixture evenly on cheese.

title: raspberry swirl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup melted chocolate chips; mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well. Spread batter into prepared pan.
Place 16 teaspoons of preserves evenly on batter; with knife swirl into batter, distributing evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Drizzle remaining 1/2 cup melted chocolate chips over brownies.

title: oat and wheat bread
directions: In large bowl, combine cracked wheat, brown sugar and salt. Heat water to boiling and stir in molasses and oil; add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside; cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup lukewarm water.
Add to wheat mixture.
Stir in 2 cups flour, blending at low speed of mixer until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium.
Add oats and 2 1/4 to 3 3/4 cups flour, stirring until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.

Turn out on floured surface and knead in remaining 1/2 to 1 cup flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Place dough in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (45 to 60 minutes). Punch dough down to remove air bubbles.
Divide dough in half and shape into two round loaves.
Place on two greased cookie sheets. Slash 1/4-inch deep lattice design in tops.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (about 1 hour).
Preheat oven to 350°. Brush loaves with beaten egg and sprinkle tops with oats.
Bake 25 to 45 minutes or until loaves are golden brown and sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool on wire racks.

title: green beans and meat (lubee ah laham)
directions: Brown meat with onions in melted butter and add spices. Combine beans with meat mixture, cover and cook for 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and water and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.
(Hint:
A little dry mint may be added to the sauce.)

title: chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef or turkey, drain. Stir in chili seasoning tomato sauce (or tomato paste and tomatoes), and kidney beans. Pour into casserole dish. Prepare corn muffin mix according to pkg. directions. Spread batter over chili mixture. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until center is firm. Top with cheddar cheese and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Measure and sift flour, spices and baking soda into a small bowl.
In large bowl cream shortening, sugar and egg until fluffy. Add flour mixture to this alternating with sour cream.
Bake in oven at 375° on greased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and shortening together in large mixing bowl.
Blend in eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: I make in my crock-pot.
Cube cheese.
Combine all ingredients and heat until melted.
If too thick for you, add another can of soup.

title: saucy minted carrots(recipe from the club meeting's herbal luncheon)
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt in a large saucepan.
Add carrots, stirring well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until tender.
Drain carrots, reserving 1 cup of liquid.
Set carrots aside and keep warm.

title: crustless bacon quiche
directions: Fry bacon in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon; drain on paper towel.
Combine eggs, milk, baking mix, melted butter and pepper in blender or mixer and blend well. Pour mixture into greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Press bacon and cheese below the surface, using back of spoon.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: scone
directions: Set enough of your flour aside to lightly coat raisins. Simply mix all ingredients, except raisins, together.
Mixture will be sticky consistency.
Fold in raisins.
Coat a bread pan with cooking spray and put your mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: swiss deer steak
directions: Place deer steak in pan.
Add onion and pepper.
Pour on tomato sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: easy fruit cobbler(blueberry-pineapple)
directions: In a 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish, mix oleo, sugar, flour and milk.
Spread fruit over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook carrots, squash and onion together until tender.
Drain water.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 the Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Melt butter in a baking dish.
Pour 1/2 the Pepperidge Farm cornbread dressing in bottom of dish.
Mix until moistened.
Pour squash mixture on top of dressing crumbs.
Sprinkle rest of dressing crumbs on next. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Mash bananas and put juice of lemon over them.
Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale together and freeze.

title: chili casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, tomatoes, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in pasta; heat through.

title: feather orange cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, honey and eggs for 5 minutes on low speed in mixer.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with water, nuts, juice and rind.
Bake in 2 waxed paper lined layer cake pans in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool. Remove from pan.
Ice with boiled frosting or confectioners sugar to which orange juice and peel have been added.

title: elegant pumpkin pie
directions: Place butterscotch pudding in saucepan.
Add spices and salt. Gradually add milk and cook over low heat, stirring frequently. As soon as mixture has thickened, remove from heat.
Add pumpkin and stir.
Put into baked pastry shell.
Cool.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie!
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls about size of big marbles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake at 325° until tops just begin to crack (about 12 minutes).
Cool.

title: omelet
directions: (You can add any other ingredients you like.)

title: beef stew
directions: Roll beef in flour and brown.
Add water, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add sliced carrots, onions, peas, potatoes and marjoram.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred
lettuce	and place on bottom of plate. Lay chips around lettuce
on
side	of
plate. Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Add taco mix according to directions. Add can of sauce. Place
desired
amount of meat on top of lettuce.
Add chopped tomatoes, sour cream and Cheddar cheese. Serve.
tags: hot dog chili sauce with onions

title: diet veggie soup
directions: Cook about 1 hour.

title: angela's muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients except fruit. Stir with whisk. Carefully add fruit and mix.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups and sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Mix all remaining ingredients well and refrigerate.
After cake cools, pour icing over cake. Sprinkle 1 pack of frozen coconut over icing.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread as 1st layer in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish.
For next layer, spread mild salsa.
Sprinkle onion, tomato, lettuce and shredded cheese, in that order, over salsa.
Chill overnight.
Serve on taco or tortilla chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk, vanilla and butter.
Cook in top of double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour in pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar and baking powder.
Spread on pie. Bake at 250° until brown.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, salt and tapioca together and then mix with blueberries.
Let blueberry mixture set 30 minutes. Put filling in unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter and add top crust to pie.
Bake in a 425° oven for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear up angel food cake in bottom of pan.
Mix package of strawberries and pack of strawberry gelatin.
Pour over cake.
Mix large vanilla pudding and pour over strawberries.
Spread small Cool Whip on top.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Serves 75 (4 ounce) glasses.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Pour melted butter over ingredients.
Add a little milk to moisten.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato and broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet with lid, melt butter in water.
Add broccoli and onion and steam about 3 minutes.
Mix seasoned crumbs with Parmesan.
Dip tomato slices in mixture and layer in pie crust.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Blend in the cream and stir in the Swiss and Gruyere cheeses.
Add broccoli mixture and turn into prepared shell.
Bake 1 hour.

title: spanish rice(known as "glutch" at our house.)
directions: Use a large covered frypan on electric skillet.
Brown meat, then sprinkle rice on top and add vegetables, ending with tomatoes.

title: peach jello
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Cool, then add the buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in Pyrex dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top and refrigerate until firm.

title: all-day-long crock-pot beef
directions: Cut beef roast into serving-sized portions.
Brown beef in a bit of vegetable oil, although you can skip this step if rushed for time.
Slice onion and separate into rings.
Dice the peeled carrots, dice the celery and slice the peppers into thin strips or circles.
Place these into bottom of crock-pot.
Sprinkle beef pieces with black pepper, minced garlic and onion soup mix.
Place on top of vegetables.

title: wazel
directions: Mix together and enjoy.
Put in 30 cup coffeepot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together well and pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mrs. smith's french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend well.
Refrigerate.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs. Beat whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks with sugar until stiff.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
Fold egg whites into
the egg yolk mixture.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: toll house pan cookie
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Cut into bars and enjoy.

title: sweet and dilly cocktail carrots
directions: You will also need 4 clean jars.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix, spoon onto cookie sheet and bake.
For added variety, add grated cheese and garlic salt.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together; then sift 3 more times.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: quick corn pudding
directions: Mix and turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Beat well with wire whip. Shake well before putting on salad.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together and mix with cornmeal.
Combine egg, milk and oil, add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened, pour in greased 9 X 9 in. square pan.
Bake. This recipe doubles well.
Oven 450°.
Time:
25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickles cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and green pepper very thin.
Add salt and let stand for 2 hours (do not drain).
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch tidbits in double boiler.
(Make sure boiler does not get hot before adding morsels.)
Use low heat to melt. Stir constantly with wooden spoon.
When creamy, add noodles and nuts.

title: cottage fried potatoes
directions: Heat oil in a large iron skillet.
Saute onions until tender. Add cooled, peeled and cubed potatoes.
Fry until browned on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
When dissolved, add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Refrigerate until thick, not congealed. Add pineapple, cherry pie filling and nuts.
Congeal.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries.
Very pretty for holidays!

title: best ever thousand island dressing
directions: In a small bowl, stir together all ingredients. Cover and chill dressing at least one hour to blend flavors.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries well on paper towels.
Combine butter, corn syrup, salt and cm sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Chill; shape small pieces on cherries, marble size.
Place on wax paper and chill. Dip into chocolate.
Store in a cold dry place for 1 to 2 weeks. Delicious for Christmas.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in one cup boiling water.
Put dissolved jello and remaining ingredients in blender.
Add a couple of drops of green food coloring to make a cool looking salad.
Blend and refrigerate until set.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time, then add vanilla, salt and syrup.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell. Sprinkle with pecans and cook 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: french style chicken with apples
directions: Spray a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Brown chicken breasts on both sides.
Remove from skillet and set aside. Stir in sliced onion, then broth and juice.
Spread apple slices in skillet.
Arrange chicken on top.
Simmer, uncovered, just until apple slices and chicken are heated through.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add all ingredients at once. Beat until smooth. Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Grind cookies in a blender.
Mix with butter and press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Slice and spread ice cream over cookies.
Melt and squeeze fudge over ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add chilies and cook 15 minutes. Drain grease. Soak tortillas in enchilada sauce.
Grease casserole. Place 3 tortillas in bottom. Put half the meat, half the cheese and half the mushrooms on top of the tortillas.
Repeat for second layer.
Pour rest of enchilada sauce on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese; set aside.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Add other mixture, then blend in Cool Whip.
Layer in container starting with pudding mixture, then Oreos, repeating ending with Oreos.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Cook onion in a tablespoon of oil over medium heat until transparent.
Add spices and chicken.
Cook 1 to 2 more minutes; set aside.
Place oil in a deep fryer or large, heavy skillet; heat to medium-high.
Carefully dip each tortilla in hot oil for a few seconds each, just to soften them up and drain on paper towels.
Divide the chicken mixture between the tortillas and roll them up, securing each one with a toothpick.
Fry the flautas until golden brown on all sides; drain on paper towels.
Serve the flautas with a dollop each of sour cream, guacamole and Salsa Fresca and sprinkle with a little grated cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: finnish turnip
directions: While turnip is hot, add rest of ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Turn into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it starts to brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: russian tea(spiced tea)
directions: Mix all the items together in a large container.
Store in large containers with lids.
To use, place 3 to 4 teaspoons mix per cup of hot water.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, milk and vanilla, stirring with spoon until blended. Add beaten egg whites, folding into mixture gently. Do not overmix. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until top of cookie is lightly browned.

title: chicken noodle creole
directions: In skillet, melt butter; add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika; add cream of chicken soup and tomato sauce.
Mix and bring to a boil; stir in lemon juice, horseradish, pimento and mushrooms.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse.
Combine noodles with skillet ingredients; spoon into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown bread("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add molasses and buttermilk.
Sift white flour with salt and soda.
Add alternately with whole wheat flour. Grease and flour bread pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl combine milk, water, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well. Pour into crust and sprinkle with nutmeg and bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Add the sugar and egg. Stir in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Add extract. Chill dough for 1 hour. Form into balls and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Frost with colored frostings and trim with nuts and candies.
These cookies also may be rolled into balls, dipped into sugar and flattened with a fork.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and oil. Beat in eggs. Add rest of ingredients. Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season and boil chicken breasts in water.
Drain and debone chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 30 minutes and crackers are brown.

title: great potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered pan.
Bake until golden brown on top and sides at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: moon baubles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Stir in flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add Tasteeos cereal and chocolate pieces just until blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and cool.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, buttermilk and eggs in a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Mix nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle nut mixture on cake mixture and swirl into cake.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. While hot, drizzle on a mixture of powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Use mixer at medium speed.
Reduce speed and add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Alternate with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Grease 8-inch tube pan. Put a layer of batter in bottom of pan, then swirl around some of the whole cranberry sauce.
Add another layer of batter and more sauce.
Add the remaining batter and swirl remaining sauce on top. Sprinkle with nuts and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: crustless mexican pizza
directions: Mix ground beef, seasoning and egg together.
Pack into baking dish and bake for 20 minutes.
Drain juice.
Cover with salsa and grated cheese and bake for another 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Combine the powdered sugar and cocoa. Set aside. Combine the cheese and butter in a double boiler. Stir until cheese melts. Add the sugar mixture, nuts and vanilla. Pour into a greased baking dish. Let fudge cool completely. Cut into squares and serve.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in 4 or 5 equal portions.
Combine flour and salt; pound meat to tender.
Flour both sides of meat (save remaining flour).
Brown meat in hot oil.
Put browned meat into baking dish.
Blend remaining flour into pan drippings in skillet.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots, onion and Worcestershire to drippings. Cook; stir constantly, until mix boils.
Pour over meat.

title: german slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion; mix well.
Bring to a boil the other ingredients.
Pour over cabbage and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Enough for church social.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour with baking soda and powder, cinnamon and salt.
Beat into butter mixture.
Mix just until flour is moistened.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: light yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add yeast to milk mixture.
Add 3 cups of plain flour; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and melted Crisco. Add additional flour.
Knead well on floured board until smooth. Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours or longer. Punch down.
Make into rolls.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: new orleans peanut butter pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, moisten crumbs with butter and put a thin layer on sides and bottoms of 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add this to the eggs.
Sift together three times flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk, then add burnt sugar and maple flavoring.
Stir well. Bake in 3 layers.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Wash chicken.
Combine rice, cream of chicken soup and water in a casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Place chicken over rice mixture.
Cook at 350° for about an hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a large punch bowl, pinch 1/2 of angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Prepare instant pudding as directed on box.
Over the cake, layer 1/2 can of crushed pineapple, 1/2 pudding mixture, 1/2 cherry filling and a layer of sliced bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
If desired, garnish with pineapple slices.
Cool for 24 hours.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add all other ingredients.
Add powdered sugar last.
Mix; press in pan.

title: citrus punch
directions: In a saucepan bring sugar and water to a boil. Cook for five minutes. Cover and refrigerate until cool. Combine juices and sugar mixture. Mix well. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale. Serve over ice. Yield 6 quarts.

title: turkey and green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, water and margarine in a large bowl until margarine is melted.
Stir in stuffing crumbs just to moisten; set aside.
tags: Stove Top stuffing mix for turkey

title: sweet alice
directions: You will need a cookie sheet.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix juices and ginger ale just before serving.
Use an extra can of pineapple-grapefruit juice with cherries for an ice ring. This amount makes about 34 (5 ounce) punch cups.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Season meat and add it to crock-pot.
Add the water.
If desired, the onion and bouillon cube may be added before adding the water.
Cover and cook on high setting for 4 hours.

title: raisin bars
directions: Place the raisins, oleo and water in a saucepan. Cover and boil together for 20 minutes. Let cool, then add the well beaten eggs, soda, salt, nutmeg, flour, sugar and cinnamon. Spread on a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut in squares after cool.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes.
Heat oil in a frying pan.
Pour milk in a bowl.
Mix salt and pepper with flour.
Dip slices of tomatoes in milk, then dredge in flour.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk per pudding directions and fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Top with 1/2 pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers and rest of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.

title: freezer punch
directions: Liquify first three ingredients in a food processor.
Add sugar and water.
Mix well with fruit mixture.
May be frozen for days.
When ready to serve, let thaw.

title: peanut butter 'n' banana bread
directions: In large bowl, stir flour, sugars, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine mashed bananas, milk, peanut butter, oil, vanilla and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove and cool.
Wrap and store overnight.
To serve, frost with Peanut Butter Frosting (recipe follows).
If desired, top with crushed peanuts and chocolate chips.
Slice to serve.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown turkey in pan.
Add chopped onion and cook until soft. Cook rice approximately 20 minutes.
Add rice to cooked turkey and onion.
Beat raw egg and stir into mixture.
Wilt cabbage leaves in a steamer for about 8 minutes.
Divide mix into 8 equal parts and roll it into the cabbage leaves.
Put into greased pan and add gravy.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set. Return to room temperature and cut into squares.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour red chili sauce on top and bake in 9x13 pan at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix together; roll in ball; roll in pecans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, then mix with soup, butter and eggs.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken bake
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed and set aside to cool.
Mix all ingredients except last ingredient.
Top with dry dressing mix or croutons.
This should fill a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: dutch peach cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan or baking dish. Wash and peel peaches in bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice to keep from darkening.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/4 cup sugar into a bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until dough is blended.
Spread dough in prepared pan.
Press peach slices into dough in rows, overlapping them slightly.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Drizzle top with butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve warm with Vanilla Sauce.

title: creole eggplant
directions: Saute eggplant and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix all ingredients in a skillet and cook, covered, over low heat until vegetables are tender (about 30 minutes). Stir occasionally. Cover with cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Sift the flour, sugar and salt and put in pie pan.
Mix the oil and milk together and add to dry ingredients.
Mix with a fork and then press around the pie plate.
Bake 12 minutes at 425° in oven or you can put crust into a microwave on High setting for 3 minutes.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place chops in casserole.
Mix in frying pan remaining ingredients.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and water.
Season to taste and add 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pitcher.
Pour into a blender; cover and blend 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.

title: sage-marinated pork chops
directions: In a self-sealing plastic food storage bag, combine oil, sherry, sage and pepper.
Add the pork chops; push out all air and seal tightly.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes to 2 hours.

title: simple banana bread
directions: With electric mixer, blend in the egg, sugar, butter or oleo, salt and flour.
Pour in sprayed or well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for one hour.

title: taco mac salad
directions: Toss together after meat and pasta cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in additional pecans and/or paprika.
Makes one large or two small cheese balls.

title: lazy brunch casserole
directions: Cook the sausage and drain.
Beat the eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer the bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a two-quart casserole.
Pour the egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until fairly firm like a custard.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Coat dates with flour.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into tube pan with removable bottom.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Use a heavy, large saucepan and bring the sugar and milk to a slow rolling boil, stirring constantly to keep milk from scorching.
Boil 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips and butter.
Stir until melted and blended well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Spread on a large, ungreased pan and when cool, cut into squares.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Stir in onions and celery.
Saute over medium heat until onions are golden brown and translucent.

title: walnut spice cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except walnuts on low speed of mixer for about 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Continue beating on high speed 3 minutes more, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into 2 prepared round cake 9-inch pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: peanutty breakfast mugs
directions: In blender, combine milk, peanut butter and honey.
Blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Pour into 4 cup glass measure; cook at High 4 minutes just until bubbly.
Pour into 4 heatproof mugs.
Top with a marshmallow puff.
Makes 4 servings.

title: betty's cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
Form into a ball or balls and roll in nuts.

title: beef macaroni tomato casserole
directions: Cook beef and raw vegetables together for approximately 20 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients well but do not beat.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: french fried okra
directions: Dip the okra into beaten egg, seasoned well. Dredge with flour, salt and pepper.
Drop in deep hot fat until brown.
Drain and serve.

title: snickers salad
directions: Chop up the Snickers and apples.
Mix with Cool Whip and chill.
Yum, yum.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: In pan bring water to boil.
Add broccoli and cauliflower, bring to boil and reduce heat and cook, covered, for 5 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water.
Separate peas by rinsing under cold running water; drain.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds and set aside to cool. Cream margarine with sugar.
Add buttermilk, cooled Bran Buds and eggs.
Mix with flour, soda and salt.
Combine remaining dry ingredients with All Bran and add to mixture.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, cheese and salt in ungreased casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix the eggs and milk together and add to the cheese mixture.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole and bake for 40 to 45 minutes until eggs are set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters and put into bag, add cinnamon and sugar.
Shake to coat.
Put in a greased tube pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over top of cinnamon sugared biscuits.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry crunch(microwave)
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in baking dish.
Layer dry cake mix and pecans over top.
Drizzle with butter.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes, turning twice.

title: smoked oyster ball
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Add salt, onion powder, garlic and Worcestershire.
Blend thoroughly.
Add oysters and blend well.
Round mixture into ball and refrigerate until hard enough to roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat the powdered sugar, eggs, 2 sticks oleo and vanilla 10 minutes.
Spread on graham cracker layer.
Spread the pineapple and bananas over the second layer and top with the Cool Whip.
Decorate with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: nut squares(yield:  3 dozen.  do ahead)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, egg yolk and vanilla. Spread evenly in bottom of well-greased jelly roll pan (or other pan with low sides).
Brush top with egg white.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cut in squares.
Store covered for 3 days before serving.

title: escarole and beans
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 6 to 8 minutes, until tender.
Add broth; bring to boil.
Add escarole and macaroni.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until escarole is wilted and macaroni is tender.
Add beans, red pepper flakes and pepper; heat through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and Italian bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Blend together butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour. Then add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake, they'll be hard.

title: "mock cocktail" scarlet daiquiri
directions: In a blender or food processor container, process cranberry juice cocktail, strawberries, sugar and lime juice until blended. Serve over crushed ice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat butter and shortening 30 seconds in another bowl.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well blended.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: fettuccine with ham and mushroom sauce
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add ham and mix well.
Prepare White Sauce Base, using 1/4 cup additional milk.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Pour over ham mixture and heat until bubbly.
Serve over hot noodles.
Garnish with parsley and additional grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup, ketchup and mustard; simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: malai murghy
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces thoroughly.
Poke pieces with fork and marinate chicken with garlic, ginger and green chili pastes, salt, pepper, and cumin powder for 2 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and apples.
Mix dry ingredients and add.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix sugar and milk. Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Break cake into bite size pieces. Add to mixture and mix together.
Pour into large bowl.
Mix thawed strawberries with strawberry glaze and pour over top. Take a spoon and let some glaze go down in cake.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans. Mix with other ingredients.
Let stand for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter in a saucepan over medium heat until transparent.
Add the beef and cook, stirring until beef is light brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook 5 minutes, then add sour cream and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice or noodles and garnish with paprika.

title: sonora chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked, then shred the meat.
Mix soups, chili, taco sauce, milk and onion.
Layer everything, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with a Mexican rice, salad and cold beer!

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Blend together the first 6 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas. Roll up and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
To serve, slice in thick slices and pass salsa for dipping.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.
Cool.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Mix; chill and serve.

title: barbecue style meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper and 1/2 can of tomato puree well.
Shape into loaf and bake in shallow pan for 45 minutes at 350°; drain fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over meat loaf and continue baking for 45 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin log(taste like carrot cake without carrots.)
directions: Beat 6 eggs until thick and lemony.
Gradually beat in 2 cups sugar.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice.

title: oneal's chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Beat in eggs. Add milk and stir until mixture is thick and creamy. Heat until mixture boils very thick, stirring to keep from scorching. Remove from heat, adding oleo and vanilla; mix until very creamy. Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: bacon rice stuffing
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving drippings.
Saute onion and mushrooms in bacon drippings until onion is transparent, but now brown.
Add rice and cook until golden.
Stir in broth, wine and seasonings.
Mix well.
Simmer until rice is tender.
Add egg, mixing lightly.
Crumble in bacon.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cream cheese burritos
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill and slice.

title: spiced almonds
directions: Toast almonds in butter over low heat.
Sprinkle with salts, ginger, nutmeg and soy sauce.
Shake pan to distribute spices. Cook and stir until nuts are dry.
Makes 1/2 cup nuts.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Work all together until it forms a stiff paste.
Press into a shallow baking pan about 1/2 inch thick and prick all over with a fork.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and continue to bake until golden but not brown (about 20 minutes).
Serve with anything.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix vinegar, Eagle Brand milk, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add this mixture to chopped vegetables and then add to cooled, drained macaroni.
(Will be real thin at first.)
Let set overnight or 4 hours.

title: christmas rusk(julekake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift together dry ingredients and add with sour cream and soda.
Divide dough in thirds.
Put in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it pulls away from side of pan; cakes should be golden colored.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and cocoa until mixture is smooth and sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs, dash of salt and nuts.
Bake pie crust for 5 minutes, then pour in cocoa mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer potatoes, onions, hamburg, rice, celery and carrots. Add salt, pepper and paprika to each layer.
Mix soup and water. Pour over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Ten minutes before serving, add slices of cheese or grated cheese.
This recipe can be made larger just by increasing all ingredients.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add flour 1 cup at a time, mixing well.
Add zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Blend.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion rings and milk, stirring well.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Place in a preheated oven at 280° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour or until brown on 350°.

title: ham hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add cheese the last 15 minutes. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Combine all in a jar and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Toss with 1 head romaine lettuce, torn into small pieces.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; cut up in small pieces. Boil spaghetti until done; drain water off.
Combine chicken breasts, spaghetti, onion, bell pepper, cream of mushroom, chicken and celery soups and pimentos.
Mix ingredients well.
Put in deep dish casserole or baking pan.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle cheese or place slices of cheese on top of casserole and melt for 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Rub with sage.
Top each with Prosciutto; secure with toothpicks.
Dust with flour.
In skillet brown with butter.
Add wine; bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until broccoli is tender, stirring occasionally.
Spoon a third of the broccoli mixture into electric blender.
Blend 20 seconds.
Repeat until all ingredients have been blended.
Pour mixture back into pot.
Stir in milk and simmer 20 minutes.
Garnish each serving with cheese, if desired.

title: cranberry pecan salad
directions: Mix jello and when it is almost set, add the other ingredients.
Can be served with whipped cream or with mayonnaise.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix together; put in greased casserole dish or pan.
Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. This casserole is great for a luncheon.
It's a hit.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients like pie dough for crumbs.
Take out 2 cups of these crumbs for top of pies.
To remainder of crumbs in bowl, add next three ingredients and mix well.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons baking soda in extra 1/2 cup hot water.
Add to other liquid mixture.
Divide liquid into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Put crumbs on top and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 375° and bake about 30 minutes or until top is dry and done.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add salt.
In a 1-cup measure cup, mix the egg and vinegar, then fill the cup with water.
Mix ingredients in cup, then add to flour.
(Do not mix too much.) Roll on flat surface.
Makes 5 pie crusts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat the shortening, butter, oil and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and then vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to batter.
Chill 2 hours.
Form into walnut size balls.
Press down lightly with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° to 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a meat loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Prick bottom of pie shell and brown for about 5 minutes. Brown sausage and add green onions.
Drain.
Beat eggs slightly and mix with milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate truffle tart
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions except add the 1/4 cup nuts and the sugar to dry mix.
Shape into 24 (3/4-inch) balls.
Press onto bottom and up sides of 24 ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Bake in a 450° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Cool in pans on a wire rack.
Remove from pans.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion until tender; add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Use a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Layer noodles, meat sauce and cheese; repeat, making 2 or 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Spread graham cracker crumbs evenly on top of butter. Spread sweetened condensed milk evenly over top. Spread chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and coconut. Top layer is walnut or pecan pieces. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown. Cool before cutting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Salt and pepper. Combine with all other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: country captain
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
(Skin chicken.)
Brown in shortening.
Remove from pan.
Add onions, peppers and garlic clove.
Saute until brown.
Add water, ketchup, curry and thyme; mix well.
Add chicken, coating each piece. Cover and bake one hour, stirring occasionally, at 350°.
Serve over rice.
Add almonds as garnish.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and add butter.
Mix together.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add crumb mixture into pan and flatten.
Save 1/4 cup for top.
Soften ice cream and add milk.
Beat pudding with milk; follow directions on box.
Blend ingredients.
Blend
Cool Whip with mixture.
Pour over cracker mixture.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Peel potatoes and slice thinly. Place in casserole dish. Salt lightly.
Place meat on top and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir to blend all ingredients well.
Set in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: gooseneck round roast
directions: Sauce:
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs, then add green chilies, Monterey and Cheddar cheeses, evaporated milk, flour and salt. Stir.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch glass casserole dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kraft dinner casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as
package directs.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add
tomatoes and green and red pepper. Cook until done.
Add to
macaroni,
then
stir
in
cheese to taste.	Garlic can be added.

title: polka dot cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate pieces, cherries and nuts.
Place rounded teaspoonfuls of dough on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with spoon.
Add liquid ingredients, stir well with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add leeks and saute 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in ham, beans and pepper.
Add enough water to just cover beans.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: 4-b's cream of tomato soup
directions: Simmer 1 hour except cream.
Heat cream in microwave and add the hot tomato mixture to cream.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: duck with peach sauce
directions: If duck is left whole, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stuff with onions, parsley and celery; roast at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.
Pour off drippings several times during roasting.

title: sausage-potato dinner
directions: Grease 10-inch pan.
Line pan with potatoes.
In saucepan, heat soup and water.
Stir in cheese.
Add cut up sausage and green pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Cover while baking.

title: pink salad
directions: Blend in cream cheese with Miracle Whip.
Mix cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Then add to cream cheese mixture. Whip the whipping cream and add food coloring.
Blend all the ingredients together. Chill.
Let stand overnight or for several hours for best results.

title: flash primavera
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; 3 minutes before pasta is done, stir in broccoli. Drain pasta and vegetables; transfer to large bowl. Set aside and keep warm. Meanwhile, in small bowl, dissolve cornstarch in water; set aside. Simmer broth and garlic in large saucepan over medium heat 3 minutes. Whisk in cornstarch mixture. Stir in mixed vegetables and spinach; cook until hot, about 5 minutes. Toss sauce and vegetables with pasta. Season to taste with salt and pepper; sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all with rotary beater.
Pan-heat about 1 inch of oil to about 350°.
Put 1/2 cup batter in funnel; drop into hot oil in 'squiggly' shape.
After about 1 minute, turn and cook 1 more minute.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar or powdered sugar.

title: ecstasy cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, sour cream and 1/2 cup water in bowl, beating well.
Stir in chocolate chips, chocolate and half the pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: bara brith(welsh christmas bread)
directions: Cover fruit with enough water to cover. Boil to tender.
Take from heat. Add butter while hot and sugar.
When cool, add lemon extract, eggs and molasses.
Add yeast, flour, salt and spices. Blend well and let rise.
Bake at 350° until brown on top and sounds hollow.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add sauce and bell pepper.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a casserole dish. Top with Cheddar.
Add remainder of mixture and top with Mozzarella.
Place biscuits over the top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Add eggs and sugar to shortening.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in water.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Divide dough in 4 parts.
Roll out to size of pie pan, cut in wedges and roll to center.
Let rise 4 hours.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes at 375°.
Yields 32 rolls.

title: grand honey ham
directions: Put flour in 1 Brown-in-Bag; shake well.
Cover entire ham with honey mustard.
Coat well.
Tie bag.
Cut 6 small slits in top of bag.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes per pound.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: fried apples
directions: Cut bacon into bite sized pieces.
Put in skillet.
Core apples and quarter.
Place apples over bacon.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Cover and fry slowly until bacon is done and apples are tender.

title: instant hot spiced tea mix
directions: Thoroughly mix al ingredients in a large container.
Then place a couple cups of ingredients in blender at a time and blend until fine.
When all has been blended, store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit medley
directions: In a large bowl, combine pie filling. Add canned fruits. Cover and refrigerate. Stir in bananas just before serving. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: baked broccoli and cheese
directions: Arrange broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese, chopped eggs and 1/2 of the onions over top.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over broccoli.
Bake for 45 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle remaining onions over dish.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: good morning christmas coffee cake
directions: Place frozen rolls in a tube pan.
Melt butter and pour over roll dough.
Sprinkle pudding mix, brown sugar and pecans.
Cover and let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple and cheese casserole
directions: Melt cheese and butter; blend well.
Stir sugar and flour into mixture.
Put apples in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour mixture over apples and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: veggie pizza(combined recipe)
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Spread out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat together mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch mix.
Cool crust.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of crust.
Add vegetables and toppings.

title: fruit frappe
directions: Dissolve 4 cups sugar in 4 cups water.
Add 4 cups cold water and 1 c. lemon juice.
Freeze overnight.

title: marjorie's brownies
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder; cream butter until soft and smooth.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, then vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Fill 1 gallon glass jar with small pickles or large pickles, sliced in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cover with mixture of 3 quarts water and 1 heaping cup uniodized salt; let set 1 week.
Drain and cover with clear water overnight (24 hours).
Drain and cover with approximately 3 quarts of water mixed with 1 tablespoon alum; let set 24 hours.
Drain.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: molasses hermits
directions: Mix together the sugar, eggs, Crisco, molasses, vinegar and boiling water in a large bowl.
Blend the dry ingredients together and stir into the molasses mixture.
If desired, stir in some chopped nuts and/or raisins.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in buttered baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine on stove the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix and melt cheese in sauce and pour on top of chicken.
Place buttered crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake crust until brown; let cool.
Mix the other ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) spring pans.
Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in walnuts, coconut, carrots and pineapple.
Pour batter into pans; place on middle rack in the oven.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until edges pull away from sides.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring, about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes; stir until gelatin is thickened. Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth.
Fold in sliced strawberries and chill.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all contents together.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread soup over chicken.
Sprinkle curry powder over soup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Sort and wash the beans.
Put into large pan and pour 8 cups of water over beans.
Boil gently until soft; takes about 2 hours. Add all other ingredients, except cilantro.
Continue to boil gently until soup is thick.
Serves 8.

title: mom's sausage balls
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients together, then roll into small balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add 1/2 stick oleo, milk, salt, pepper and sugar to squash; then add eggs and onion.
Combine cheese and almonds.
In an oiled baking dish, layer squash first, then cheese and almond mixture.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and melted 1/2 stick oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barley soup
directions: Soak barley 2 hours before you start cooking.
Next, cook barley for 1 hour in 3 cups of water and then wash it.
Mix the barley with the broth, chicken pieces and onion.
Add grated carrots for color and cook for another hour.
Add milk; bring to a boil and serve it.
Enjoy the soup!

title: quick and beefy pasta dish
directions: Cook macaroni.
Place in bottom of buttered 6 quart casserole dish.
Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Add mushroom soup. Simmer.
Place meat mixture on top of pasta.
Layer green beans and corn over meat mixture.
Pour mushrooms over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cover and cook onions in margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until tender, 20 to 30 minutes. Add water, pepper, thyme, bay leaf and broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add sherry and stir.
Turn oven to broil; ladle soup into 4 ovenproof crocks.
Top with toast and cheese; brown under broiler.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until used.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: auction sale soup
directions: Mix all ingredients. Heat until hot. (Using crock-pot is great!) This is great soup. Enjoy!

title: avocado mushroom piquant
directions: Peel and slice avocados.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Peel caps if necessary.

title: herb bread
directions: Grease a round casserole dish.
Separate biscuits, standing on sides, forming a circle in dish.
Mix ingredients and spread between and on top of biscuits.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: ground round steak
directions: Shape into flat loaf. Salt and pepper to taste. Broil for doneness. Top with sour cream and horseradish.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Whip ingredients in a blender until light.
Serve with warm biscuits.

title: naomi's chi chi's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer uncovered 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Ladle into jars; seal.
Process 10 minutes in boiling hot water bath.
Yields 8 to 10 pints.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Good dip for veggies or chips.

title: cheesy meatballs
directions: Mix soups, Cheez Whiz, tomatoes and chiles in blender.
Put half of meatballs in crock-pot, then half of sauce.
Put rest of meatballs, then rest of sauce.
Leftover sauce makes delicious dip for chips.

title: gourmet carrots(for those who do not like carrots)
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in salted water until tender. Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble.
Chop onions and saute in butter or bacon grease until clear.
Do not drain. Add brown sugar and stir to dissolve.
Drain carrots and add to bacon onion mixture.
Stir to cover carrots.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries, apple and sugar and let stand in fridge overnight.
Then add the Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cream sugars, Crisco, eggs, peanut butter, salt, vanilla, baking soda and flour.
Roll dough in small balls, then flatten by pressing a floured fork across each way.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
These cookies burn easily.

title: cheesy chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine soup and bouillon in a saucepan, whisking to blend. Add all ingredients with chicken and noodles added at the very end.
Garnish with parsley.
Can be made ahead and reheated but do not boil.

title: red lobster cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, water and cheese.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: jewell city corn bread muffins
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Add cream cheese; beat well.
Dissolve gelatin and add to soup mixture along with remaining ingredients.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: smothered steak
directions: Brown steak in skillet of hot oil (after rolling in seasoned flour).
After just browned, remove from skillet.
Make a thickening gravy with oil and leftover flour.
Pour in milk until thin.
Replace meat in skillet and simmer until gravy thickens. Serve with homemade biscuits!

title: special sweet potato bake
directions: Place sweet potatoes and enough water to cover in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cover and cook for 25 to 35 minutes or just until tender.
Drain; cool slightly and peel.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour, alternating with 7-Up.
Add flavoring and mix for 3 minutes.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Test to see if it is done by inserting a toothpick in the middle and it comes out clean.

title: rumaki(6 servings)
directions: Slice chicken livers into 3 pieces each; fold each piece over a water chestnut.
Wrap a strip of bacon around the liver-chestnut cone, pinning each kabob with a toothpick.
Marinate 1 hour in soy sauce, ginger and curry powder.
Drain; broil in a preheated broiler, turning frequently until bacon is thoroughly cooked, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken south of the border
directions: Pour boiling chicken broth over crunched Doritos.
Place chicken on Doritos.
Sprinkle onion and Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Add in layers:
mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Cheddar cheese soup.
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish for 30 minutes.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Lay Twinkies in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cook pie filling using 3 cups milk.
Cool slightly. Pour over Twinkies.
Add pineapple.
Spread with large container of Cool Whip.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: yam pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in order given.
Blend about 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pastry.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: baked oriental chicken
directions: Dredge chicken pieces with mixture of flour, Season-All and pepper.
Carefully fold under ends of chicken to form a rounded ball.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan.
Place chicken pieces in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting several times.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine melted margarine with stuffing and put in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish, reserving 1 cup for topping.
Mix together zucchini, carrots, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with reserved stuffing.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix altogether.
Jello will set.
To make jello, add 1 cup hot water and 1 cup cold water (use part of juice from pineapple for cold water).

title: homemade frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine sliced fruits in a large bowl.
Mix 7-Up, orange juice and sugar and pour over fruit.
Place foil muffin cups in muffin pans.
Spoon in mixture and freeze.

title: before breakfast
directions: Toast muffins and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top muffins with sausage.
