Mix beaten eggs, milk, pepper and mustard; pour over muffins and sausage.
Cover with grated cheese.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal gravy
directions: Heat drippings.
Add cornmeal.
Brown, then add water slowly and stir continually.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: salmon bake
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Toss together with croutons, parsley and onion.
Add eggs, soup, milk and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
May be garnished with thin slices of lemon overlapping; sprinkle with parsley.

title: easy baked chicken kiev
directions: Stir together the 4 tablespoons softened butter of margarine with the parsley and oregano.
Spread about 1/2 tablespoon of this mixture across each cutlet, about and inch from lower edge.
Lay a strip of cheese over butter mixture.
Fold lower edge of cutlet over filling, then fold up sides and roll up to enclose filling. (Use toothpicks to secure, if necessary.)
Dip each bundle in melted butter, then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink at 425°.

title: tomatoes, country style
directions: Beat together garlic, parsley, salt, cream cheese and basil. Cut tomatoes into 12 even 1/2-inch thick slices.
Spread 6 slices with 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Top with tomato slice.
Dip each in flour, egg mixture and bread crumbs.
Fry on both sides over medium heat in butter and oil until brown.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
Take out desired amount and add necessary water to form dough.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Stir together the cream cheese, milk, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken, apple, celery and green onion. Makes about 2 1/2 cups or enough for 30 small cream puffs or about 18 heart-shaped biscuits.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Mix chicken with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Lay out flat crescent rolls.
Put 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture on each one and roll up.
In medium saucepan, add soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour half of soup mixture into ungreased square dish.
Put rolls in and cook at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Use remaining sauce as gravy and top with remaining cheese.

title: payday bars
directions: Add marshmallows to top of crust when taken out of oven while still hot.

title: cheese-potato chowder
directions: Cook potatoes (onions and celery) in salted boiling water until tender.
Do not drain.
In a different pan, cook butter and flour until melted.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese; stir until thickened.
Add cheese just to melt.
Combine contents of both pans and stir.
Serves 4 as a hearty soup.
Doubles easily.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Prepare layer cake as directed and cool.
With fork, punch holes in cake and top with pineapple.
Prepare pudding as directed on box and mix in cream cheese. Spread this mixture on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: no-sugar cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients for three minutes on low heat.
Add margarine.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen. These freeze well.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add lemon juice, water, grated peel of 1 lemon.
Cook until thick.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar.
Fold into the lemon mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook first first ingredients together until potatoes are done, 20-30 minutes.
Add 2 cans cream of chicken soup and velveeta and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar, milk and cocoa together over medium heat. Let it
come to a full boil and boil for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from
heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted. Add oatmeal and stir until coated good.
Drop by spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: skillet meat balls
directions: Mix and make into small balls, brown, drain.

title: sweet russian chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves with small amount of water.
Pour over chicken and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blender bearnaise sauce
directions: Blend in the blender; pour into a container and refrigerate.

title: ethel's pudding dessert
directions: Mix as for pie crust flour, ground nuts and oleo.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool in refrigerator.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Add this on top nut crust.
Make chocolate instant pudding; add on top and refrigerate.
Make vanilla pudding; add on top of chocolate pudding, then add Cool Whip and chopped nuts on top.
Cool and serve.

title: meal-in-one beef casserole
directions: In hot shortening, saute chopped onion and ground chuck until lightly browned, stirring with a fork.
Add salt, pepper, dill seed, chicken soup, corn, mixed vegetables and sour cream.
Spoon into baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate.
About 30 minutes before serving, heat oven to 350°, uncover casserole and sprinkle onion rings over top.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot, covering loosely with foil after 15 minutes to prevent overbrowning of onion rings. Makes 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together placing bacon on top. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: micro fudge
directions: Melt butter in microwave in a safe mixing bowl.
Take out and mix in powdered sugar, cocoa, nuts and milk.
Put back in microwave 3 minutes.
Add in vanilla and pour in buttered pan. Cool in refrigerator about 5 or 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 squares.

title: michele's snowballs
directions: Cream sugar
and
butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients,
a
little
at
a time.
Roll into bite-sized balls. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in 10x sugar once while still warm
and once again when cooled.
Store in a tin can.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts.
Blend well chill.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place sesame seed on baking sheet; bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pisto manchego
directions: In heavy 12-inch skillet, heat olive oil over high heat until light haze forms above.
Add onions, zucchini, peppers and salt and stir together.
Cover pan and reduce heat to lowest possible point. Cook for about 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile place tomatoes in 1 to 1 1/2-quart saucepan and bring to boil over moderate heat, stirring and mashing them against sides of pan.
Cook briskly uncovered, until most of liquid in pan evaporates and tomatoes become a thick fairly smooth puree or use 1 can tomato puree.
Stir tomato puree into vegetables.
Then pour in the beaten egg, stirring constantly. Simmer about 1 minute.
Taste for seasoning and serve at once. Garnish the top with hard-boiled egg.

title: fig-berry preserves
directions: Mix sugar, Jell-O and figs and cook until thick.
Will taste like strawberry preserves.
Cook at least 25 minutes after it comes to a boil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in oil.
Drain off.
Place chicken in covered dish.
Let chicken bake until almost done.
Add mushroom soup and milk; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Let cook until chicken is tender and soup has made gravy.
Cool.
Serve.

title: cannon balls
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Drain well and cool.
Combine sausage, dry Bisquick and cheese.
Mix well.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn slaw
directions: Combine sour cream, Miracle Whip, mustard, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in large bowl; mix well.
Add corn, carrots, green pepper and onion; mix well.
Refrigerate until serving time. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hot cinnamon twisters
directions: Preheat oven for 30 minutes to 425°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Heat and melt butter in small pan (low heat).
With hands, flatten biscuits.
Dip in butter, then cinnamon, 2 or 3 times.
Put on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: robbie's crispy spinach
directions: Wash spinach carefully and drain it.
Beat eggs and add the cornstarch.
Season according to taste.
Heat the oil in a frying pan and when it is hot and ready, deep-fry the spinach one by one. Wait until it is golden brown.
Drain the excess oil in paper towel before serving.

title: crab and shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into ball (may have to put in freezer for a little while to make it easier to work with).
Put on cocktail sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and carrots.
Fold in flour and carrots.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Ice with Carrot Cake Icing.

title: coconut fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add fruit mix, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well. In another bowl cream oleo, sugar, eggs and lemon extract.
Mix.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with orange juice.
Put into a 10-inch tube pan greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
When cake is done turn out on wire rack until cold. Garnish with candied fruit or nuts if desired.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers upside down in cupcake liners.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Brown
meat
and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook down.
Serve on buns with cheese.
Good as taco meat for in shells.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Mix well and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: cheese and egg brunch
directions: Cube bread the size of a quarter.
Place half in 3-quart buttered casserole.
Over this, in layers, arrange mushrooms, olives and grated cheese.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water; drain.
Meanwhile, cook onion in 3 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, cheese and carrots.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole. Toss bread stuffing mix with 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Spoon over carrot mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until thoroughly heated, about 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together (except butterscotch chips) by spoon.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: west texas spaghetti
directions: Fry together meat, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Drain fat. Add soup and seasonings.
Cook spaghetti, add to meat mixture. Layer half of mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of cheese and dot with sliced olives.
Repeat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Allow full hour to warm at 300°.

title: honey dressing for fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add vinegar, lemon juice, onion and honey.
Beat well.
Add 1 cup salad oil.
Beat well. Makes 1 pint; will keep in refrigerator forever!

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together as package directs and pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Spoon over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan to cool completely.
Store in refrigerator before serving.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water to a boil in a heavy skillet.
Add sugar and syrup, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Boil until it spins a thread from a spoon when lifted from the pan.
Add peanuts and cook slowly until they turn a golden brown.
Remove from heat. Add butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir very quickly.

title: 7 day pickles(christmas pickles)
directions: Step 1:
Pack cucumbers, salt and boiling water in a crock for 7 days; drain.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours; drain.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: In large skillet, scramble eggs with 3/4 cup half and half. Remove and set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Mix soup with 2/3 cup half and half and set aside.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg and mix well.
Blend flour, salt and baking soda into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and drop by tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter 'n fudge ripple pie
directions: Chill the crust while preparing filling.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla; beat at medium speed until smooth and well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into crust.
Spoon chocolate randomly over filling. Gently pull knife through chocolate to marble.
Freeze at least 2 hours or until firm.
If frozen overnight, let stand at room temperature about 15 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unfold crust and place on an 11 x 13-inch pan, pushing up the sides and closing perforations.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes. Burns quickly.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together and spread over the crust and refrigerate. Before serving, add vegetables.
You may add any vegetables you like.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sweet potatoes.
In a large skillet, heat ingredients and stir Tang and brown sugar until dissolved.
Add sweet potatoes and cook for 10 minutes.
Glaze all sides.

title: easy teriyaki chicken and(brown rice or white)
directions: HEAT oil in large nonstick skillet on medium heat.
Add chicken; cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes or until cooked through.
ADD 1-1/2 cups water, teriyaki sauce and garlic powder to skillet; stir.
Bring to boil.
STIR in rice, broccoli & peanuts.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german dewberry or apple pie
directions: Arrange fruit to cover the bottom of an unbaked pie crust (use fresh apples, sliced thin)).
Blend rest of ingredients, except butter and cinnamon.
Pour over fruit, then dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until center is firm, not runny.

title: potato latkes
directions: Brown onion in skillet.
Add to shredded potatoes that have set 10 minutes after shredding.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet (enough to cover bottom).
Drop by tablespoon. Fry, turning once.
Use spatula to flatten slightly.

title: quiche
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, milk and egg.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: rio grande ruffles
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir milk and cornstarch until smooth. Add oleo and salt, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in corn, ham pieces and cheeses.
Remove from heat.
Stir until cheeses melt; toss with cooked pasta and corn chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesy barbecue beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add green pepper and cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in corn, barbecue sauce, chili powder and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour half of the meat mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with half of the cheese spread.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, until onions are golden brown.
Serve over buns, cornbread or rice, if desired.

title: ann's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add chili beans, ground beef and tomato juice.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini 5 minutes.
Cut cheese; put over zucchini in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over all the bread crumbs.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients.
Put over top of zucchini.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp oreganata
directions: Mix together equal amounts of butter and oil.
Add oregano, parsley, salt and pepper and a generous amount of fresh chopped garlic.
Pour over raw, shelled shrimp.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs and broil for 5 minutes.

title: fudge marble squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and put in oven for 5 minutes.
Swirl chips through dough with a knife.
Return to oven and bake for 15 minutes; cool and cut in squares.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix.
Dip anything you wish to fry.

title: easy caramel apple cheesecake
directions: Mix caramel dip with apple filling. Spoon 1/2 of the mixture into the crust. Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add eggs and beat well. Pour over apple filling. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until center is set; cool.

title: jezebel dip
directions: Stir all together.
Spoon over Philly cream cheese that is room temperature and serve with crackers.
Makes a lot and keeps long in fridge.

title: hot punch
directions: Pour fruit juices into 12-cup Regal coffeemaker.
Place remaining ingredients in coffee basket.
Cover and plug in; complete the cycle as for coffee.
Remove basket as soon as perking stops; discard spices.
Serve in heated mugs.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cider punch
directions: Pour cider over sherbet in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale. Float lemon slices on top.

title: hostess twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise in half.
Arrange Twinkies halves into Pyrex oblong baking dish.
Spread pudding over Twinkies.
Spread pineapple, followed by pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with pecans.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain, debone and flake salmon.
Mix together with all other ingredients except garnishes.
On a pretty platter, mold mixture into a fish shape.
Arrange almonds to resemble scales down the back of fish design.
Use slice of olive for eye.
Chill until serving time. Serve with buttery crackers.
Refrigerate covered. This is low in salt, sugar and fat.
Very good for diabetics.

title: nibbling bits
directions: Melt the chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine over low heat.
Pour the mixture over the cereal and coat well, stirring carefully.
Coat the mixture with powdered sugar.

title: pet sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water until tender; cool slightly.
Place cooked and peeled potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs (one at a time). Mix in spices, salt and Pet milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake on preheated cookie sheet in center of oven for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust shells

title: grammy's potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Drain liquid.
Quickly beat in the 2 eggs.
Add milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Heat some shortening in a shallow frying pan.
Spoon a small amount of potato mixture onto hot shortening.
Fry until golden brown.

title: pie pastry
directions: Blend together well; roll into desired shapes.
Will roll out thin and handle well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, both sugars and the pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour; gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Pour small amounts of this mixture over beaten egg yolks.
Mix. Pour both mixtures together over heat until real thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: apple cake and icing
directions: Cream eggs, oleo and sugar until fluffy; add flour and remaining dry ingredients.
Add apples.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cutout sandies
directions: Grind the 1/2 cup pecans with a food grinder, food processor or blender.
Combine ground pecans, flour and baking powder.
In a large mixer bowl beat butter and shortening until butter is softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, sour cream and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or until easy to handle.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and set aside.
Work brown sugar gradually into margarine until creamy.
Beat together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add applesauce.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to the applesauce mixture.
Drain raisins and then add to the cake mixture; add nuts.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done when tested with a wooden toothpick.

title: easy chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Pour all ingredients in a mixer bowl and mix real well. Grease and flour a Bundt pan (or use nonstick spray).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Don't overcook, the moister the better.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Barely cover blackberries with water and bring to a boil.
Mix flour and sugar together and put in blackberries.
Bring to a boil again.
Add butter.
Let cool before pouring in pie crust.
Put top pie crust on and sprinkle with sugar and melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: easy dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand for 30 minutes in refrigerator for flavors to blend.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients on stove top.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Transfer to a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place crescent rolls over top.
Top with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: tallorene
directions: Fry onions in fat; add meat and chili powder.
Cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook noodles separately until tender (drain).
Add to first mixture and season with salt.
Add corn, olives, pimentos and garlic and place in buttered casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes and serve.

title: (no bake) oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Beat well.
Pour into a buttered pan and cut into squares or drop spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: pork chops & fried cabbage
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of oil. Once browned, place cabbage, onions and mushrooms on top of pork chops. Cover with water and place lid on pan. Cook on low heat about 35 minutes. Season with salt and peppers to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except spaghetti) thoroughly.
Cook spaghetti or noodles until done.
Then mix with mixture of ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean stand-by
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onion rings.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings on top for the last 15 minutes of baking time.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain the first 6 ingredients well and put in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to boil, then cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti per package directions.
Do not overcook.
Pour spaghetti into colander.
Pour tomato juice into same pot; bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and drop cubed cheese into tomato juice.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour spaghetti back into pot with cheese and juice.
Ready to eat.
Better if served immediately.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a fluted pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Place defrosted strawberries, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and salt in large bowl, beating about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add whipped cream and vanilla extract.
Pour into pastry shell.
Freeze and garnish.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup butter and powdered sugar until blended.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix in another bowl the rhubarb, 1/2 cup flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, salt and eggs.
Blend and place over the crust in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve chilled.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well, but do not beat more than absolutely necessary.
Add vanilla and pour mixture into a 9-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 25 minutes longer or until the filling is firm.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream
butter;	add
sugar and cream together.	Add the eggs, one
at
a	time,
beating	after each egg.
Add flour, gradually after each egg.
Add vanilla;
pour into steeple pan lined	with waxed
paper.
Grease
pan	first.	Place in cold oven, temperature at 300° and bake 1 hour.
Then raise temperature
and
continue
baking 40 minutes.
Never look until time is over.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel yams.
Cut in slices and cook until tender. Drain and put into baking dish. Dot with butter.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant. Slice 1/4-inch thick and soak in bowl of salted, cold water (1 tablespoon in 1 quart water) for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, plunge tomatoes into boiling water and then into bowl of cold water to loosen their skins. Peel tomatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices. Drain eggplant. Rinse with fresh water. Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°. Place one-third of eggplant slices in dish. Top with half of tomato slices and sprinkle with half of Swiss cheese and then 1/3 cup Parmesan. Repeat procedure, ending top layer with eggplant. Dot with butter and pour tomato sauce on top. Cover with bread crumbs and sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake 1 hour. Let eggplant stand 15 minutes before cutting. Serves 4 to 6.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine sugar and beat until yellow.
Pour hot, but not boiling, milk slowly over mixture beating constantly. Add salt and vanilla.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake until custard is firm.

title: baked sausages
directions: Mix together
for
the
sauce and pour over sausages in shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except the kisses.
Roll into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press 1 kiss on each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch delight
directions: Put ice cream and sherbet in punch bowl.
Break into pieces with spoon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until ice cream and sherbet are partly melted.
Yield: 40 servings.

title: artichoke bites
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 by 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325 degrees.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces with fancy toothpicks for appetizers or serve larger squares without toothpicks for brunch.

title: cranberry black cherry salad
directions: Combine and put in square Pyrex dish.
Cut in squares; serve on lettuce topped with mayonnaise.
Good Christmas salad.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt and stir in milk slowly.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add mixture to egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add butter and vanilla and cool.

title: easy coconut and pineapple cake
directions: Rice and raisins with cinnamon, sugar and butter.
We kids loved this made by our Mother.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and milk.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir and pour over brownies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, syrup and vanilla.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: italian capocollo with eggs
directions: Pour oil in frying pan, and arrange slices of capocollo in oil.
Break 1 egg over each slice of meat.
Sprinkle very lightly with salt and pepper.
Fry gently until egg white is set.
Remove with pancake turner, and serve immediately.
Serves 1.

title: lemon flake cookies
directions: Add Cool Whip to the slightly beaten egg.
Add cake mix and stir.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon into powdered sugar and roll into balls. Press on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes. Should be light lemon color.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with sugar on top; set aside.
In saucepan, combine dressing ingredients.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir evenly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put in casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 300° or until golden brown.

title: rock cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift 3 cups flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Add to egg mixture. Add the 1/2 cup flour to the raisins and pecans.
Stir into other mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will not look done.

title: cheese ball
directions: In blender chop well, bell pepper, onion, salt, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Blend in cheeses.
Mix well.
Roll into ball.
Chill.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine flour and seasonings; roll meat in mixture. Preheat frypan to 340°. Place cover in Spatter Shield position. Add fat; when melted, add meat. Brown, turning to brown all sides. Add onion, garlic and mushrooms (drain liquid from mushrooms and use as part of liquid or if using tomato soup, just add to mixture). Saute until partially tender. Add liquid, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and green pepper. When boiling, turn dial to simmering point. Cover; close vent and simmer until meat is tender. Spoon off excess fat. Stir in sour cream. Heat at low simmer; do not boil. Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Let cool; add peanut butter, vanilla and salt; beat until creamy. Pour into buttered pan (let cool).

title: golden punchgroves, texas
directions: Mix above ingredients and when ready to serve, add two (2) bottles of Ginger Ale or 7-up.

title: red rice
directions: Cook meats (bacon and rib tips) until done.
Add tomato paste, onion, celery,
green pepper, salt and pepper to taste. Partly cook rice, drain and mix with all ingredients including sausage (diced).
Put in
baking dish and cook in oven at 300° until rice is done.

title: divine fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in the microwave.
Add a couple drops of cooking oil and add peanut butter.
Place over heat and stir.
Add other ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: alberta toomey's corn custard
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar and cornstarch.
Add corn, milk and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: To make extra good, add 1 cup chocolate or peanut butter chips.
Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Chill for 4 hours. Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: deon's goulash
directions: Saute hamburger in 1 teaspoon of oil; drain meat.
Add all ingredients in saucepan; cook 15 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Chop eggs; add celery and pickle.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add to eggs and mix carefully.
Serve as a salad on crisp lettuce or as a filling for sandwiches.

title: carolina chicken
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Remove wing tips and neck to make stock. Combine salt, pepper and milk.
Dip chicken in milk; dredge in flour and remove excess flour.
Deep fry at 350° until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover bottom of roasting pan with stock. Place chicken pieces in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: weight watcher's chicken breasts with raisin sauce
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season chicken with dash each of salt and onion powder.
Tuck ends of each breast under to form rounded mound.
Cover with skin and place in nonstick baking pan and bake about 25 minutes or until done.
Remove and discard skin.
While chicken is baking, prepare fruit sauce.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup
of
the
cake
mix
for
topping.
Mix balance of cake mix with 1/2 cup of the melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugars and cream well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend.
Add lemon flavoring and sifted dry ingredients.
Stir until dough is formed.
(If eggs are large, more flavoring may be needed.)
Drop by teaspoonful or roll out and cut into shapes.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes in a 350° oven.
Also makes good filled cookies.
Makes 14 dozen cutout or drop cookies.

title: lemon-cheese salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved.
Cool until it begins to set.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: tar baby pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well.
Slice banana into pie crust.
Pour Cool Whip over sliced bananas.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: corn bake
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in the margarine (not until brown, just clear).
Add the eggs.
Add the kernel corn, cream-style corn and pimento. Add the corn muffin mix.
Blend the sour cream through mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use toothpick test for doneness.
Continue baking until toothpick tests clean.

title: funny cake
directions: Cream shortening sugar and eggs.
Add flour, milk, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Put batter in 2 large 10-inch unbaked pastry shells.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 2 (8-inch) pie pans. Divide mixture and fill pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: tiramisu
directions: Separate the whites in a separate dish; blend on high speed until fluffy and creamy.
Beat the egg yolks in sugar, then mix coffee and rum.
Add the cheese, then at the end, add the egg whites, folding in slowly.
Make 4 cups of strong, perked coffee. Dip the biscuits in very quickly; do not soak.
Line them up in a regular size Pyrex dish, then pour half of the filling on top. Repeat another layer of biscuits; top with the remainder of the filling.
Sprinkle a lot of cocoa on top; refrigerate for at least 4 hours or more.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking soda and baking powder in large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Batter will be thin. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan, 30 to 35 minutes for round pans.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add water, beaten eggs and vinegar; cook until thick.
Add dry mustard, celery salt, evaporated milk and salad dressing (Miracle Whip).
Beat together until well mixed.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In a mixing bowl combine about half of the flour, brown sugar, shortening, molasses, egg, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium to high speed until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until set and tops are crackled.
Cool cookies on a wire rack. Makes about 48.

title: tater tot meal
directions: Layer 1/2 of the Tater Tots in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Dot with soup.
Spread beef evenly over this layer, then dot with corn.
Sprinkle with cheese, then bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: hollywood squares
directions: Mix together melted butter, peanut butter, confectioners sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: healthy banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder, nutmeg and a dash of salt; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat together egg whites, sugar and banana.
Add oil and mix well. Stir flour mixture into banana mixture.
Fold in currants and nuts.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in the pan.
Remove and cool on a wire rack.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook cut up broccoli until crisp-tender.
Add chopped eggs and chopped olives.
Mix with mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Chill.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish sauerkraut, then Swiss cheese, 1/2 bottle of dressing, corned beef, then remainder of dressing. Place cubed rye bread on top and pour melted margarine over the bread.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Place butter or margarine, green beans and salt in covered saucepan.
Turn to high heat until steaming, then turn to a lower heat and cook until tender.
Meanwhile, fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of the reserved bacon fat.
Add vinegar, pepper, green beans and buttery liquid in saucepan.
Serve topped with crumbled bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides; place in baking dish.
Mix bread cubes or poultry stuffing, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over chops and stuffing.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: pickle green beans
directions: Place grape leaf, pepper, garlic and dill in bottom of jar; pack tender green beans in jar. Bring water, salt and vinegar to rolling boil. Boil for 5 minutes; pour over beans in jar. Seal and put in oven on baking sheet at 250° until beans change color. Ready to eat in about 2 weeks.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add seasoning to chicken while cooking. Remove chicken and save broth. Bring broth to a boil; should be about 2 cups broth. Mix flour, both kinds, together and cut in Crisco. Mix until crumbly. Combine eggs, water and salt. Mix with flour mixture until stiff dough forms. Roll out real thin and then cut into strips, 3 to 4-inches long. Drop strips into boiling broth; add chicken. Cook for 15 to 18 minutes. Don't put
a lid on them while cooking because if you do, they will be tough.

title: mom-mom's corn chowder
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and onion in medium saucepan with water; cook until just tender.

title: white chocolate clusters
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave at 30 second intervals until melted. Stir in Rice Krispies, pecans, and pretzels. Stir until coated. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper or foil. Let set until firm.

title: great american meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, milk, Heinz 57 sauce, salt and pepper.
Shape into a loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
Allow meat loaf to stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate.

title: golden rod
directions: Hard boil eggs.
Make one cup medium white sauce by mixing margarine and flour over medium heat, and adding milk.
Cook until thickened.

title: old english prime rib
directions: Select choice prime rib or standing rib.
Season meat with Worcestershire sauce, paprika, m.s.g. and salt and pepper.
Rub this seasoning into meat.
Put rock salt on bottom of roaster pan. Dampen rock salt with water.
Place meat in standing rib position.
Cover meat completely with damp salt.
Place pan, uncovered, in 500° preheated oven 12 minutes per pound for rare; 20 minutes per pound for well done.
Remove from oven.
Break salt crust with mallet.
Brush any residue from meat and eat.
This does not leave any salt flavor.

title: nacho frio-dip
directions: Spread bean dip
on
bottom
of pan.
Mash avocados and add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and spread on bean dip.
Mix taco seasonings with sour
cream.
Spread
on top of avocados.
Top with the tomatoes, onions, black olives and shredded cheese.

title: light cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add broccoli and next 3 ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Garnish each serve with 1/2 teaspoon shredded cheese.
Makes 4 servings; 166 calories per cup; 3.1 grams of fat.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, bring 1 1/2 quarts of water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add seasonings and shredded cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter. Stir to boiling.
Slowly add water to flour, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring rapidly.
Cook and stir soup until it is the consistency of heavy cream.

title: chocolate cake with fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a heavy saucepan. Stir in milk. Add butter; bring to a boil. Cover and cook over medium heat 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until spreading consistency. Yield: 2 1/4 cups.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all together; put in an 8-inch square pan or 9 x 13-inch pan (if making larger amount.
Top with crushed potato chips; sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into a ball. Roll in parsley and paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Brown the ground beef and drain.
Cut up the onion and grate the cheese.
Pour half of the meat in skillet.
Pour half of the corn meal mixture over the meat.
Sprinkle all the cheese on the batter.
Sprinkle the other half of the meat.
Next add all the onion and then cover with remaining half of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: viennese potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins.
Bring mixture of vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, water and olive oil to boil; simmer 10 minutes. Peel potatoes while still slightly hot and slice into heatproof bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over potatoes.
Add the onions. Carefully blend and let marinate for 1/2 hour covered at room temperature.
Add crumbled bacon.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix chopped broccoli, onion, cottage cheese and melted oleo. Add corn muffin mix and beaten eggs.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 19-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture tests done.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison in 1/2-inch wide and 1/4-inch thick strips.
Mix salt, pepper, onion powder, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Pour on meat and marinate overnight. Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Dry in oven on very low heat (about 250°) for 5 to 6 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour, egg yolks, milk and vanilla. Beat whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into other mixture. Put into unbaked pie shell and bake at 245° for 45 minutes.

title: french toast for large group
directions: Melt butter and sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread in pan. Blend eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread.
Cover; put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let set 20 minutes.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat well all ingredients except flour.
Then add flour.
Make small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick. Set aside and cool. Line cooled pie crusts with sliced bananas, 1 cup grated coconut and 1 cup nuts. Pour pineapple mixture over the above when cool and let stand in refrigerator. Before serving, top with whipped cream.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo and crumble cookies.
Add raisins, pecans and milk to this.
Knead together.
Put mixture into a container and press it down.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into smaller portions.
Wrap in wax paper and foil, then freeze.

title: sausage bread
directions: Chop mushrooms finely. Chop garlic very fine.
Brown sausage. Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Drain thoroughly, then combine. Roll out thawed bread dough.
Spread mixture of egg and Parmesan cheese onto dough.
Put sausage mixture on dough and add cheese.
Fold ends of dough in and sides out, or try to roll it. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with pinto beans!

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large casserole.
Toss all together.
Mix corn flakes with oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead of time or can be frozen.
Let potatoes thaw a little; will be easier to mix.

title: shrimp mull
directions: Fry
bacon
and
crumble.
Add onion to bacon drippings and saute until golden.
Add green peppers and celery.	Simmer with lid on pan for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until thickened.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Cook meats together and drain.
Add cheese; turn heat back to low to get cheese all melted.
Add oregano, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Put spoonful of mixture on party rye on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Put cookie sheet in freezer until solid.
Mistakes can then be put in plastic bag and kept frozen until ready to use.
Can be kept frozen for a few months.
When ready to serve, use Pam spray on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: india relish
directions: Wash, trim and quarter vegetables. Put vegetables through food grinder, using medium blade; drain, discarding liquid. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in saucepot; heat to boiling. Add vegetables; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Continue simmering while quickly packing one clean, hot jar at a time. Fill to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables. Cap each jar at once. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: chocolate peek-a-boos
directions: Heat
milk
and
butter
in a saucepan just to boiling. Add sifted
dry ingredients, all at once, to hot milk.	Cook, stirring constantly,
until
mixture leaves sides of pan in a smooth, compact
ball.
Remove from heat.
Blend in eggs, one at
a
time, beating well after each until mixture is smooth. Add
vanilla; mix
well
and
cool.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop
by
scant teaspoonfuls,
2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in	a
375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until
golden
brown. For
drier	Peek-A-Boos,
turn off oven after
baking,
prick cookies with a sharp knife and let stand in
oven
for
5 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cool;	sprinkle
with more
confectioners
sugar,
if needed. Makes 6 dozen.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Lightly scramble eggs.
Mix all ingredients together, using 3/4 of cheese.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg, oil and pumpkin. Stir thoroughly.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: spicy chicken gumbo
directions: Saute 1 first-four ingredients in large heavy kettle.
Blend in flour.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add 2 - 3 cups cooked chicken, diced.
Simmer briefly.
To serve:
mound cook rice in the center of a bowl.
Pour gumbo around.
Enjoy.

title: corn and pepper saute
directions: Cut the peppers into thin strips.
There should be about 2 cups.
In a large skillet, heat the olive oil and butter over medium heat.
Add the peppers, corn and onions.
Sprinkle with the garlic, cumin, if used, salt and pepper.
Cook, shaking skillet occasionally, 6 to 8 minutes or until heated through and pepper strips are tender-crisp.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate, topping and milk; mix well. Spoon into pie shells.
Chill, covered, until firm.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small, heavy saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with 1/3 cup sweetened milk.
Spread evenly on bottom of pie shell.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and butter.
In large bowl, beat eggs with remaining sweetened milk, water and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour into pie shell; top with pecans.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool and chill.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.

Make a white sauce of butter, flour, broth and milk. Stir in chicken and mushrooms. Mix with noodles, 1/2 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Turn into round 2-quart glass casserole. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 400° until bubbly hot (about 20 minutes). Serves 6.

title: fluffy sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until plump.
Drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Add brown sugar and raisins to liquid and boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir into raisin mixture, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Slowly add eggs, stirring until eggs are cooked (mixture will be thick).
Cool.
When cool, add sour cream.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill.
Just before serving, top with remaining whipped topping.

title: crab mold
directions: Soften gelatin in the water.
Heat soup and gelatin mixture. Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Whip until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm. Serve with crackers.

title: lower-calorie brownies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin pie(yields one 9-inch pie)
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Pour into deep 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until set in center.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: After frying pork chops, put in a baking pan.
Pour rest of ingredients over pork chops.
Bake in oven at 375° to 400° until tender.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Put roast into crock-pot.
Mix gravy mix and water together and pour over roast.
Cook on high 6 to 8 hours.
Can add potatoes 2 hours before roast is done.

title: satin cake
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, butter and orange rind in bowl.
Beat 5 minutes.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add alternately with orange juice and water.
Beat egg whites until frothy and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in cake batter.
Bake in layers for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cacciatore chicken
directions: In a 1 3/4-quart microwave-safe pan, combine mushrooms, green pepper, onion and water.
Cook, uncovered, on 100% power for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, olives, tomato paste and garlic powder.
Add chicken breasts to casserole, turning to coat with sauce.
Arrange meaty portions toward outside edge of casserole.
Cover and cook on 100% power for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender. Serve with rice or pasta, if desired.
Makes 4 servings, 176 calories.

title: crab ball
directions: Drain liquid from 1 can of crab meat.
Mix drained crab meat with cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and minced onion.
Form ball.
Drain second can of crab meat.
On a sheet of waxed paper, spread crab meat.
Roll ball in crab meat, covering entirely. Wrap ball in waxed paper; chill for 2 hours.
Mix catsup, horseradish and lemon juice for sauce.
Serve with sauce on top. Spread on crackers.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Sprinkle with the first 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Spread the chilies in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining chilies over meat.
Combine the remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over meat and chili layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes and cut in squares.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry-pineapple salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in a bowl.
Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple with juice. Fold in nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: speed bake yeast
directions: Break yeast into 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Mash the potato. Add potato water and sugar.
Add softened yeast to potato mixture. Add enough lukewarm water to make mixture equal one quart.
Keep in warm place (about 80°) until next morning.

title: sizzling dash burgers
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly.
Shape into 3/4-inch patties and grill or broil.
Makes 6 juicy burgers.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots cross wise on the bias in 1 inch chunks.
Cook covered in boiling salted water until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Meanwhile combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, and ginger in small saucepan.
Add orange juice and cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Boil one minute then stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.
Serves 4.

title: ambrosia(fruit salad)
directions: Drain cans and combine in a large bowl.
Add bananas, strawberries and marshmallows.
Drizzle with honey and dust with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sour cream to the desired texture.
Add pecans and serve.

title: yummy cake
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and cook at 300° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not flour pan.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Boil roast beef until it falls apart. Saute onions. Combine all ingredients. If too dry, add beef broth. Serve on buns with coleslaw.

title: mimi's plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and cinnamon.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Mix together. Add nuts.
Grease a bundt pan and pour in the mixture. Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: juicy pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops approximately 10 minutes on each side in vegetable oil.
Pour cans of soup over top. Cover and simmer for approximately 40 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain, if necessary.
Add drained corn, salsa, mayonnaise, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Crush corn chips.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a gallon bag. Working with one can at a time; Remove, separate, and cut into 4 pieces.
Coat with melted butter. Add to bag with sugar mixture.
Close bag and shake to coat pieces. Grease bunt pan. Gently press pieces into pan. Repeat with remaining cans of biscuits. Bake in Preheated oven at 375° for 45-55 min.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add flour, beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Put batter into a large greased tube pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; save broth.
Cool chicken and remove from bone in small pieces.
Mix in bowl along with Veg-All, cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup and one soup can of broth from chicken.
Pour into long dish or pan.
Mix flour, milk and Wesson oil together and pour over top.
Bake until crust is brown in 425° oven.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Cook spinach in small saucepan according to the directions on package. Drain well and set aside. In small saucepan, on low heat, combine milk and cream cheese, stirring until cream cheese melts to a smooth consistency.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, milk/cream cheese mixture and spinach; mix well.
Place pie shell on a cookie sheet and pour mixture into the shell.
Bake for 45 minutes and serve warm.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted margarine and 2 eggs.
Spread into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla together.
Spread on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, oleo and egg.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, melt over low heat the peanut butter chips, corn syrup, vanilla and 1/4 cup oleo.
After this has melted, add the dry roasted peanuts and Rice Krispies.
When cake is done, pour miniature marshmallows on top, then pour melted mixture over the top.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar, flour and salt.
Let stand 15 minutes. Add water.
Prepare pastry and fill with rhubarb mixture.
Dot with oleo.
Top with second crust
and cut slits for steam to escape.
Seal and flute.
Bake at 400° for gas stove for 50 minutes or at 350° for electric stove for 35 minutes.

title: potato ham scallop[
directions: In saucepan melt butter, stir in flour; off of heat stir in milk keeping smooth.
Return to heat stirring constantly until thickened.
Off heat, stir in cheese, fold in potatoes and ham. Add salt and pepper and enough paprika to give a pretty pale color. Turn into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° about 20 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry onions and garlic in oil.
Add meat and work loosely.
Add tomatoes, corn and pepper.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs; add milk and corn meal.
Combine ingredients.
Put in baking pan, 15 x 10 x 2 1/4-inches deep.
Sprinkle black olives on top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 20 people.
Great dish for potlucks, family gatherings or picnics.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, mixing well, then add the vanilla.
(If using self-rising flour, omit salt and baking soda.)
Put in cold oven (do not preheat oven).
Bake at 325°.

title: football fan's delight (dip)
directions: Place hamburger in crock-pot and cook until done.
Place Velveeta cheese in crock with cooked hamburger.
When cheese melts, put Ro-Tel tomatoes in mixture.
Stir together.
Serve with tortilla chips and jalapeno peppers (peppers optional).

title: an easy cake
directions: Take cake out of oven and pour pineapple over cake.
Let cool. Then pour pudding over cake and pineapple and cool.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and refrigerate.
May sprinkle coconut on top.

title: barbara whitman mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients; add flour and nuts.
Add cream, then knead a few times.
Chill dough in shape of log in wax paper. Let set overnight.
Slice and place on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until browned.
Remove; sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still hot.
Freezes very well.

title: garlic pecans
directions: Roast in shallow pan at 300° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir until coated with butter.
Salt to taste.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups milk in saucepan with sugar.
Dissolve cornstarch with 1/2 cup milk and add to the milk at boiling point. Cook until thick; remove from stove.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into the lightly baked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° or until it starts bubbling.

title: berry apple compote
directions: Combine liquid in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add fruit and apples.
Bring to a boil; simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Make a paste of cornstarch and water and stir into the sauce.
Stir constantly until thickened.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (1 3/4-quart casserole).
Stir in raw macaroni.
Slice cheese; cut each slice in four.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and milk.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir while baking.
Bake until golden brown.

title: microwave barbecued chicken
directions: Skin chicken pieces and remove all fat.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken in 6-quart casserole. Cook 45 minutes on medium.
Remove from microwave and turn chicken in sauce.
Turn dish in microwave to finish cooking.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves approximately 6. Cooking time:
1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on microwave.

title: ike's bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cooled milk in a large mixing bowl. Crumble yeast into the mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add shortening.
Work flour into the mixture, until dough is easy to handle.
(May need a bit more than 7 cups flour.)
When dough is smooth and elastic, place in a greased bowl, turning once to bring greased side up.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again 30 to 45 minutes, until nearly double in bulk.
Divide dough in half. Let rest, covered with a towel, for 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise for about 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is neatly browned.

title: tex-mex peanuts
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in 8-inch skillet over medium heat until golden brown; discard garlic.
Stir peanuts and chili powder in skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until peanuts are warm, about 2 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place pared, sliced fruit in 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing until crumbly. Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake about 30 minutes, until fruit is tender and topping is golden.
Serve alone or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sopa de tortilla
directions: In blender container, combine undrained tomatoes, onion, garlic, cilantro and sugar. Cover and blend until nearly smooth. Turn into a large saucepan; stir in chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch wide strips. Fry in 1/2-inch hot oil 45 to 50 seconds or until crisp and lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels. Divide fried tortilla strips and cheese among soup bowls.
Ladle soup over. Serve immediately.

title: monkey balls
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon; cut each roll into 1/4.
Roll each one in mix; toss into greased Bundt pan.
Pour rest of sugar and cinnamon mix on top.
Melt margarine and brown sugar to make a syrup.
Pour syrup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert on plate.
Be careful, sugar is still hot. Enjoy!
It's a great finger picking dessert.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well.
Cook on High in microwave for 12 to 15 minutes, stirring every 3 or 4 minutes.
Cool and knead until pliable. Store in airtight container.

title: italian chicken with artichokes
directions: Drain the artichokes, saving them for later and combine 1/2 of their liquid with the oil in a 10 to 12-inch skillet.
In a paper bag, place the flour and chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake and coat chicken well.
Brown the chicken on each side in the skillet over medium-high heat for about 5 to 7 minutes per side. Transfer the chicken to a 3-quart casserole dish.
Combine all the other ingredients, except the artichokes and parsley sprigs, in the browning skillet.
Simmer over medium-low heat for 10 minutes. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Add the artichoke hearts and adjust seasonings, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.
Serve the chicken on a deep platter with buttered vermicelli in the middle, surrounded by the chicken and sauce. Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serves 8.

title: taquitos (flautas)
directions: Stir-fry meat with onion and spices to taste.
Soften corn tortillas in hot oil just until pliable.
Fill corn tortillas with meat mixture and roll into tight rolls.
Secure with toothpicks and fry in hot oil until crispy.
Serve with sour cream, salsa, guacamole and/or con queso.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Peel eggplants and cut into round slices (about 1/8-inch thick). Dip in milk and egg batter, then dip in flour and fry until brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 5 loaf pans or 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese pinwheels
directions: Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions.
Knead on floured board for 1 minute.
Roll out into thin rectangle. Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll as for jelly roll; cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until brown.

title: quick easy cookies
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt the butterscotch in a double boiler on medium heat or follow directions on package for microwave.
Add peanuts and stir. Add chow mein noodles and stir until mixed well.
Drop by teaspoonful on aluminum foil or wax paper.
Allow to harden.

title: vermicelli cold salad
directions: Mix together. Don't add tomatoes until ready to serve.
(Best if sits overnight in refrigerator.)

title: aunt elsie's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch pans. Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add chocolate.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt alternately with sour cream.
Blend on low speed and add hot water.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving part of the noodles to put over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey and stuffing quiche
directions: Mix together stuffing and melted margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine turkey and cheese; spread in bottom of baked stuffing crust.
Beat together eggs and milk or cream; pour over meat mixture.
Reduce oven heat to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until set in center (when a knife inserted comes out clean).
Cool slightly before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: marshmallow delights
directions: Finely chop celery sticks into very small pieces.
Mix milk and butter together.
Boil sweet potatoes.
Mix sweet potatoes (already beaten) with milk and butter.
Put sweet potatoes in a pan.
Melt marshmallows on top of sweet potatoes, then sprinkle on your cinnamon.
Add crushed celery sticks on top.
Prep: 25 minutes.

title: beef and potatoes(a quick dish)
directions: In skillet, put 1 cup water and salt.
Add hamburger meat, in small pieces.
Add onions, garlic, steak sauce and potatoes.
Cook until meat is done.
Then add cream of mushroom soup.
You may have to add a can of water.
Cook until gravy is thick.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Melt oleo in pan and pour flour mixture over melted oleo.
Spread peaches on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: roman stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes; brown in butter and oil over medium heat; remove.
Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley and pepper; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add wine, broth and cheese; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in meat and mushrooms.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Add water or broth if needed.
Serves 4.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place in shallow pan. Top with diced tomatoes, 1/2 c. Thousand Island dressing and sliced Swiss cheese. Sprinkle with buttered rye bread.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain uncooked spinach.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill 12 to 24 hours before serving with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix all ingredients together (except crackers) in a small bowl.
Pour over crackers and toss until crackers are evenly coated.
Put crackers in a baking pan with edges and bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: mexicali chicken 'n rice
directions: Blend seasonings and rub into chicken pieces.
Place chicken, skin side up, in a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with onions and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Bring the cream to a boil.
Turn the heat down.
Add the cheese.
Add salt and pepper.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth (no lumps).
Pour ingredients into a spring-form pan.
Bake on 325°
for 1 hour (may need a little longer depending on oven). Then turn off oven and leave cheesecake in oven for 1 more hour. Cool and refrigerate.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Time: 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients except lasagna noodles. Use 1 1/2-quart rectangular dish.
To layer (makes 2 layers): noodles, ground beef mixture, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Full power 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: glazed tangerine ambrosia
directions: Place tangerine segments in a large seive over bowl; set aside. In a small sauce pan, combine sugar and water, bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil rapidly for 2 minutes.

title: lasagna ii
directions: Brown meat.
Simmer 10 minutes with the sauce, water and seasonings.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 sauce mixture, 1/2 noodles, 1 cup cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat and end with the sauce and Mozzarella.
Top with Parmesan.
Cover and bake with foil at 350° for 1 hour; let stand 10 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients all together for 2 minutes, then add the nuts.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Frost cake while still warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate bar, marshmallows and milk in double boiler until melted.
Remove from heat and cool until thick.
Stir in whipped cream.
Pour into shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with more whipped cream and shaved chocolate when serving.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sour cream; sprinkle with bacon and green onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake potatoes at 300° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: reuben salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine the greens, tomatoes and croutons. Add strips of beef, cubed cheese, sauerkraut and dressing. Toss gently to coat.

title: creole shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute shrimp in oleo until pink, stirring all the while.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until wilted, not brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Melt bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add with all other ingredients except parsley and green onion.
Steam in rice cooker until rice is cooked.
Remove from pot.
Add green onion.
Add parsley.
Toss with fork and serve.

title: dietetic punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add Sweet 'N Low and other ingredients. Pour into 1/2-gallon milk cartons and freeze. Remove from freezer and serve when slushy.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Place green onions and slice
Roll up and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: breakfast or supper casserole
directions: Cook sausage or turkey in skillet over medium heat, stirring until crumbles and no longer pink, drain well.
Place bread cubes in lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Sprinkle the cheese evenly over the bread, top with sausage or turkey.
Whisk together the eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage or turkey mixture.
Cover and chill casserole for 8 hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until set.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6-8 serving.

title: see's fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in microwave or over stove in double boiler.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and beat well.
Mix chocolate mixture with powdered sugar and blend well.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered platter or pan and chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cake mix, Cool Whip and pecans. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over the top.
Melt 2 sticks margarine and spread over cake mix.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: midwestern baked chili
directions: In a skillet cook turkey, celery, onion, green pepper and squash until turkey is no longer pink.
Add chili powder, pepper, cumin and red pepper.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and beans.
Heat; set aside.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Spoon muffin batter into lightly greased 12 to 16-ounce individual casseroles.
Spoon chili mixture over batter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Top with sour cream if desired. Makes 8 main dish servings.
Contains 511 calories per serving, 20 grams of fat and 5 grams fiber.

title: dried beef cheese ball or log
directions: In medium bowl, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and beef until combined well; refrigerate. When chilled, shape into a ball or log. Roll in parsley flakes and press a few cherries into top for decoration. Serve with crackers. Makes 1 cheese ball or log.

title: krendal (russian rolls)
directions: Heat half and half until scalding; add to sugar, butter and salt.

title: lemon-lime marinated fruit
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine honey and remaining ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk.
Pour over fruit.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally. Yields 12 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Note:
Use as much cheese as you like.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown onion and ground beef; drain.
Add potatoes, onion and cabbage.
Cover with water.
Simmer at least an hour.
Add bouillon to taste.

title: kansas chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in one bowl and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Then add 1 cup boiling water to mix and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sun maid raisin brown betty
directions: Arrange alternating layers of apples and raisins in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with sugar blended with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add water.
Top with crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Cover.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 30-40 minutes until apples are tender.
Remove cover.
Continue baking to brown top. Serve with cream or hard sauce.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Add orange juice and lemonade to the 3 cups of ice cold water. Dissolve sugar in cranberry juice.
Mix together and chill. Before serving, add Catawba juice.
Great for weddings and bridal showers.
Serves 24.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg; cut in 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts. Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remaining firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables and barley are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: savory cheese loaf
directions: Cut crust from loaf of French bread.
Slice to bottom.
Put thin sliced Swiss cheese between bread slices.
Mix 1/2 cup softened butter with 1 tablespoon mustard and 1 tablespoon poppy seed.
Spread all over bread, top and sides.
Lay 3 or 4 slices of bacon on top.
Tie with string lengthwise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all the ingredients together until fluffy.
Pour into a large, greased casserole dish, then sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom cary's cranberry salad
directions: Grind
cranberries
and
oranges
in
food grinder.
Put sugar over
fruit
and let stand for one hour.
Add celery and nuts. Stir
until sugar is mixed well.
Then add cooled jello. Put
in salad mold and chill until set thoroughly.
(You grind the oranges with the peeling on.)

title: bake shop doughnuts at home
directions: Dissolve yeast into lukewarm water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening to hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm, then beat in eggs.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat thoroughly.
Stir in dissolved yeast. Add just enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: skillet chili con carne
directions: In skillet, brown beef	and cook onion with chili until tender (use shortening if	necessary).
Stir to separate meat. Add soup and beans.	Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 cups.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and lemon extract; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time; continue beating after each addition.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture; beat well.
Pour into large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, depending on your oven, until cake tests done.
(Suggest testing with toothpick after 1 hour and 15 minutes).

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Put in fridge and wait five to ten minutes to serve.
